msgid "Artrax"
msgstr "Artrax"

#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:113
#, fuzzy
msgid "Saurian Juveniles"
msgstr "Juveniles saurien"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:325
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The seven saurian matriarchs lie somewhere in this swamp. With most of their "
"warriors away at war, they will be vulnerable."
msgstr ""
"Les sept matriarches des sauriens se trouvent quelque part dans ce marais. "
"Puisque la plupart de leurs guerriers sont partis au combat, elles sont "
"vulnérables."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:329
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The Blackcrests have good reason to fight, but none of this should concern "
"saurians — they’re not usually invaders. I need to figure out what’s going "
"on with this alliance and put an end to it."
msgstr ""
"Les Crêtes-noires ont de bonnes raisons de se battre, mais tout cela ne "
"devrait pas concerner les sauriens — ce ne sont généralement pas des "
"envahisseurs. Je dois comprendre ce qui se passe avec cette alliance pour y "
"mettre fin."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#. in this string, $companion_name is female (probably "Lynyan")
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:335
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"female^That is, if we can find their camps. This ruined place was once a "
"great city of their kind — even what little remains is too vast for us to "
"scour it all. This is where you said your guides would meet us, "
"$companion_name?"
msgstr ""
"Enfin, si nous réussissons à trouver leurs camps. Cet lieu en ruines était "
"autrefois une grande ville de leur espèce — même ce qui en reste est bien "
"trop étendu pour que nous puissions tout fouiller. C’est bien ici que vos "
"guides devraient nous retrouver, $companion_name ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#. in this string, $companion_name is male
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:341
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"That is, if we can find their camps. This ruined place was once a great city "
"of their kind — even what little remains is too vast for us to scour it all. "
"This is where you said your guides would meet us, $companion_name?"
msgstr ""
"À condition, bien sûr, de trouver leurs camps. Ce lieu en ruines était jadis "
"une grande cité de leur espèce ; même les vestiges qui subsistent sont trop "
"vastes pour que nous puissions tout explorer. C’est là que tu as dit que tes "
"guides nous attendraient, $companion_name ?"

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:346
#, fuzzy
msgid "You’re almost there! Jus’ a lil bit further... almost..."
msgstr "On y est presque ! Encore un tout petit effort…"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:360
#, fuzzy
msgid "Rendezvous with your companion’s guides"
msgstr "Rendez-vous avec les guides de votre compagnon"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:414
#, fuzzy
msgid "Hey, what—"
msgstr "Hé, quoi—"

#. [event]: id=activate_poachers
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:418
#, fuzzy
msgid "Gonnin"
msgstr "Gonnin"

#. [event]: id=activate_poachers
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:423
#, fuzzy
msgid "Milyn"
msgstr "Milyn"

#. [event]: id=activate_poachers
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:428
#, fuzzy
msgid "Barin"
msgstr "Barin"

#. [message]: speaker=Barin
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:434
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Well well, look what the cat dragged in. You’re a little far from home, "
"scholar!"
msgstr ""
"Eh bien, eh bien, regarde ce que le chat a ramené. On dirait que tu es un "
"peu loin de chez toi, l’érudit !"

#. [message]: speaker=Barin
#. "protection" is a reference to a "protection racket", where organized crime will extort money from victims. Barin isn't actually proposing a protection racket - he's genuinely offering to help Delfador - but it's meant to sound ambiguous and suspicious
#. this is also a reference to a similar scenario in Delfador's Memoirs, where bandits actually are trying to rob you (unless you're on Easy, in which case they join you)
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:440
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"There’s lizards out here... and robbers too. T’would be a shame if something "
"happened to you. Maybe you oughta have our protection — for a price."
msgstr ""
"Il y a des lézards ici... et des voleurs aussi. Ce serait dommage qu'il "
"t'arrive quelque chose. Peut-être devrais-tu t'en remettre à notre "
"protection pour éviter des ennuis — moyennant finance."

#. [option]
#. $fee is very likely between 24 and 100
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:455
#, fuzzy
msgid "Pay $fee gold (learn to recruit Poachers)"
msgstr "Payer $fee pièces d'or (apprenez à recruter des braconniers)"

#. [option]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:461
#, fuzzy
msgid "Attack"
msgstr "Attaquer"

#. [message]: speaker=Barin
#. in this string, $companion_name is female (probably "Lynyan")
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:487
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"female^Great! Rest easy now that you’ve hired us; we’ll guide you ’round the "
"swamp and make sure nothin’ happens to you or the rest of your coin! "
"$companion_name said yer looking for them lizards, yeah?"
msgstr ""
"Super ! Repose-toi bien maintenant que tu nous as engagés ; on te guidera "
"dans le marais et on veillera à ce qu'il ne t'arrive rien, ni à toi ni à ton "
"argent ! $companion_name a dit que tu cherchais des lézards, c'est ça ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Barin
#. in this string, $companion_name is male
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:493
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Great! Rest easy now that you’ve hired us; we’ll guide you ’round the swamp "
"and make sure nothin’ happens to you or the rest of your coin! "
"$companion_name said yer looking for them lizards, yeah?"
msgstr ""
"Parfait ! Repose-toi maintenant que tu nous as engagés ; on te guidera à "
"travers le marais et on s’assurera que rien ne t’arrive, ni à toi ni à ton "
"argent ! $companion_name a dit que tu cherches des lézards, c’est bien ça ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Barin
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:509
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"...what, you didn’t think we was trying to rob something, did ye? Naw, I’m "
"your guide. I’d never hurt a friend of $companion_name’s."
msgstr ""
"...quoi, tu ne pensais pas qu’on essayait de te voler quelque chose, si ? "
"Nan, je suis ton guide. Je ne ferais jamais de mal à un ami de "
"$companion_name."

#. [object]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:516
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Poachers are general-purpose nighttime archers, with numerous-but-weak "
"ranged strikes and unusually good defense in swamps."
msgstr ""
"Les braconniers sont des archers nocturnes polyvalents, dotés de nombreuses "
"attaques à distance peu puissantes et d'une défense exceptionnellement bonne "
"dans les marais."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:540
#, fuzzy
msgid "Insolent fools, I am no sickly scribe, easy pickings for the robber!"
msgstr ""
"Insolents imbéciles, je ne suis pas un scribe maladif, une proie facile pour "
"le voleur !"

#. [message]: speaker=Barin
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:544
#, fuzzy
msgid "Whoah, hey uh, what’s going on?"
msgstr "Oh là là, euh, qu'est-ce qui se passe ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:548
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You bandits trifle with an archmage of Wesnoth, famed and powerful. Step "
"forth and meet your doom!"
msgstr ""
"Vous, bandits, vous vous frottez à un archimage de Wesnoth, célèbre et "
"puissant. Sortez et faites face à votre destinée !"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:554
#, fuzzy
msgid "Defeat the bandits"
msgstr "Vaincre les bandits"

#. [message]: speaker=$unit.id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:585
#, fuzzy
msgid "Ughhh..."
msgstr "Arghhh..."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:593
#, fuzzy
msgid "I’m gettin’ out o’ here!"
msgstr "Je me tire d'ici !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:602
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Serves them right, preying on innocent travelers... Now, where’s these "
"guides of yours we’re going to meet?"
msgstr ""
"Bien fait pour eux, à s'en prendre à des voyageurs innocents... Au fait, où "
"sont ces guides que nous sommes censés rencontrer ?"

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:606
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Umm... you know what, I’m thinkin’ we’re better off hunting them saurians "
"all on our lonesomes instead. I’m still gettin’ paid after all this, right?"
msgstr ""
"Euh… tu sais quoi, je crois qu’on ferait mieux de chasser ces sauriens "
"chacun de notre côté. Je serai quand même payé après tout ça, n’est ce pas ?"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:620
#, fuzzy
msgid "Defeat three of the seven saurian leaders"
msgstr "Vaincre trois des sept chefs sauriens {PROGRESS_STRING}"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:637
msgid "(3 remaining)"
msgstr ""

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:639
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Surprise attack: The saurians will not spot you until you approach within 4 "
"hexes of a matriarch."
msgstr ""
"Attaque surprise : Les sauriens ne vous repéreront pas tant que vous ne vous "
"approchez pas à moins de 4 hexagones d’une matriarche."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:660
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"That saurian has different markings than the others I’ve seen, and is "
"somewhat smaller. A juvenile or invalid, perhaps?"
msgstr ""
"Ce saurien présente des tâches différentes de celles des autres que j’ai "
"observées, et il semble un peu plus petit. Un juvénile ou un invalide, peut-"
"être ?"

#. [message]: speaker=second_unit
#. delfador has just attacked an unarmed saurian
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:668
#, fuzzy
msgid "The monssstersss hunt usss for sssport! Flee, flee!"
msgstr "Les monssstres nous pourchasssent pour le plaisir ! Fuyez, fuyez !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:672
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"They really are unarmed juveniles! Hang on a minute, they’re not dangerous, "
"maybe we should just let them be."
msgstr ""
"Ce sont vraiment des juvéniles inoffensifs! Attendez une minute, ils ne sont "
"pas dangereux, peut-être devrions-nous les laisser tranquilles."

#. [message]: speaker=$found_unit.id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:695
#, fuzzy
msgid "We’re under assssault! Sssound the alarm and rally our warriorsss!"
msgstr ""
"Nous sssommes attaqués ! Sssonnez l’alarme et rassemblez nosss guerriers !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:699
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"They’ve spotted us! The time for stealth is past; now come the fire and the "
"flame!"
msgstr ""
"Ils nous ont repérés ! Le temps de la discrétion est révolu ; place au feu "
"et aux flammes !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:722
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"There are few villages to be found here, but look! We have stumbled upon an "
"oasis.\n"
"\n"
"Like villages, an oasis will heal anyone standing on it. Unlike villages, an "
"oasis provides neither income nor protection."
msgstr ""
"Il y a peu de villages dans les parages, mais regarde ! Nous avons découvert "
"une oasis.\n"
"\n"
"Comme les villages, une oasis soigne ceux qui y reste. Cependant, à la "
"différence des villages, elle n’offre ni revenu ni protection."

#. [message]: speaker=$unit.id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:752
#, fuzzy
msgid "Who are you! Why bring death into my homesss..."
msgstr "Qui êtes‑vousss ! Pourquoi sssemez‑vous la mort dans nos foyersss…"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:756
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I am Delfador, war-mage of Wesnoth! Abandon the Blackcrest orcs to death by "
"Wesnoth’s spears, or I will visit upon you the same destruction your allies "
"would bring to us!"
msgstr ""
"Je suis Delfador, mage de guerre de Wesnoth ! Laissez périr les orcs des "
"Crêtes-noires sous les lances de Wesnoth, ou je vous infligerai la même "
"destruction que vos alliés voudraient nous imposer !"

#. [message]: speaker=$unit.id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:760
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"But tribe Earth-Becomes-Clay mussst fight Wesssnoth! The Great One has "
"commanded us!"
msgstr ""
"Mais la tribu Terre-Deviens-Argile doit combattre Wesnoth ! Le Grand Être "
"l'a ordonné !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:764
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The “Great One”? I had thought you matriarchs led your tribe. Tell me, "
"elder, who is this of which you speak?"
msgstr ""
"Le « Grand Être » ? Je pensais que vous, matriarches, guidiez votre tribu. "
"Dites-moi, l'ancienne, de qui parlez-vous ?"

#. [message]: speaker=$unit.id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:768
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"We sssauriansss are finally united... the Great One makesss usss... "
"ssstrong..."
msgstr ""
"Nous autres, sssauriens, sssommes enfin unisss… Le Grand Être nous rend… "
"forts…"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:774
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Alas, she has expired. Her wounds were too great. But we have learned much — "
"we must capture another matriarch to find out who this ’great one’ is."
msgstr ""
"Hélas, elle est morte. Ses blessures étaient trop graves. Mais nous avons "
"beaucoup appris — nous devons capturer une autre matriarche pour découvrir "
"qui est ce « Grand Être»."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:776
msgid "(2 remaining)"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:793
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You are beaten, lizard! Your ’great one’ commands you to kill my people; "
"tell me who or what the ’great one’ is, and your life shall be spared."
msgstr ""
"Tu es vaincu, lézard ! Ton « Grand Être » te force à massacrer mon peuple ; "
"dis-moi qui ou ce qu’est ce « Grand », et je te laisserai la vie sauve."

#. [message]: speaker=$unit.id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:797
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Curssse you! We are all nothing but wormsss before her... she will dessstroy "
"you in an inferno of flamesss!"
msgstr ""
"Maudit sssois-tu ! Nous ne sssommes rien que de misérables vers face à elle… "
"elle vous consssumera dans un torrent de flammes !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:815
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"And I shall destroy YOU in an inferno of flames if you don’t tell me what I "
"want to know!"
msgstr ""
"Et je vous détruirai dans un enfer de flammes si vous ne me dites pas ce que "
"je veux savoir !"

#. [object]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:826
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/utils/spellcasting.cfg:768
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/utils/spellcasting.cfg:1354
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/utils/spellcasting.cfg:1837
#, fuzzy
msgid "fireball"
msgstr "boule de feu"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:843
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Wait, what! I wasn’t actually going to— that wasn’t supposed to happen! "
"Where did that fireball come from!"
msgstr ""
"Attendez, quoi ! Je n’allais pas vraiment… ça n’était pas censé arriver ! "
"D’où vient cette boule de feu ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:847
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"...it seems I’ve spent so much time building my power that I neglected the "
"finer arts of control. Methor would be ashamed... I must redouble my efforts."
msgstr ""
"…il me semble que j’ai passé tellement de temps à accumuler de la puissance "
"que j’en ai négligé les subtilités de sa maîtrise. Methor aurait honte de "
"moi… je dois redoubler d’efforts."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:868
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"...decades ago, an elvish seer told me about <i>“the dark swamp”</i>, and "
"that I must <i>“endeavour to bestow not destruction with that fire that I "
"possess, but the gleaming light of truth instead.”</i> Surely this was not "
"the event that she referred to?"
msgstr ""
"…il y a des décennies, une devineresse elfe m’avait parlé de <i>« du sombre "
"marais »</i>, et que je devais <i>« m’efforcer de ne pas répandre la "
"destruction avec ce feu que je possède, mais plutôt la lumière éclatante de "
"la vérité. »</i> Ça ne doit certainement pas être l’événement auquel elle "
"faisait référence ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:872
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Garard thinks little of such superstition, but I have done my best to follow "
"that cryptic advice. Yet I confess I understand precious little of what she "
"was trying to say. Why must seers always speak in riddles? It is hard to "
"think clearly, especially in times of crisis..."
msgstr ""
"Garard ne croit guère à ces superstitions, mais j’ai fait tout mon possible "
"pour suivre ces conseils mystérieux. Et pourtant, je confesse que je saisis "
"à peine ce qu’elle cherchait à dire. Pourquoi les devins parlent-ils "
"toujours aussi énigmatiquement ? Il est difficile de garder l’esprit clair, "
"surtout en période de crise…"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:875
msgid "(1 remaining)"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:898
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Cease your fighting, matriarch, for you have been bested! Heed this warning: "
"answer my questions or be burned to ashes!"
msgstr ""
"Cessez le combat, matriarche, car vous avez été vaincue ! Prenez garde à cet "
"avertissement : répondez à mes questions ou je vous réduirai en cendres !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#. Delfador was worried he would accidentally shoot a fireball, but he didn't
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:918
#, fuzzy
msgid "(There we go. Both power and control.)"
msgstr "(On y arrive. Puissance et maîtrise en même temps.)"

#. [message]: speaker=$unit.id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:922
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Mothersss protect me, can it be? Are you a sssecond great dragon of fire!? I "
"am blessssed to sssee sssuch thingsss in my time..."
msgstr ""
"Mèresss, protégez-moi, est-ce possible ? Ssseriez-vous un sssecond grand "
"dragon de feu !? Je sssuis bénie de voir de telles merveilles de mon temps…"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:926
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"A drago— your great one is a dragon!? ...yes, I am a great dragon as well. "
"Do you not see my fire? Do you not see my flight?"
msgstr ""
"Un drag— votre « Grand Être » est un dragon !? …Oui, je suis également un "
"grand dragon. Ne voyez‑vous pas mon feu ? Ne voyez‑vous pas mon vol ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:936
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Now you shall tell me where I may find the dragon —the other dragon. The two "
"of us have much business together."
msgstr ""
"Maintenant, vous allez me dire où je peux trouver le dragon — l’autre "
"dragon. Nous avons beaucoup d’affaires à régler ensemble."

#. [message]: speaker=$unit.id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:940
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Oh, Great One, I hear you and obey! Follow me, and I will guide you to your "
"sister."
msgstr ""
"Oh, Grand Être, je vous écoute et j'obéis ! Suivez-moi, je vous conduirai "
"vers votre sœur."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:967
#, fuzzy
msgid "Everyone, keep moving! We’re running out of time."
msgstr "On se bouge tous ! Le temps presse."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:1015
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"What’s this? Filthy humans grubbing around in our swamp? These lizards are "
"Blackcrest property!"
msgstr ""
"Qu'est-ce que c'est que ça ? De sales humains qui fouillent dans notre "
"marais ? Ces lézards appartiennent au clan Crêtes-noires !"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:1019
#, fuzzy
msgid "They ssstrike at the matriarchsss! We ssshall ssslay them all!"
msgstr ""
"Ils sss'en prennent aux matriarches ! Nous allons tousss les anéantir !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08_Ruins_of_Saurgrath.cfg:1023
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The main orcish army has caught up to us! Even if we defeat this vanguard "
"and flee onwards, we’ve missed our chance to break the saurian alliance..."
msgstr ""
"L'armée orque principale est sur nos talons ! Même si nous parvenons à "
"vaincre cette avant-garde et à fuir, nous aurons raté notre chance de briser "
"l'alliance saurienne..."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08x_Field_Hospital.cfg:4
#, fuzzy
msgid "Field Hospital"
msgstr "Hôpital de campagne"

#. [message]: speaker=Lionel
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08x_Field_Hospital.cfg:110
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Ah, much better. Thanks again for the healing, old man, but I’m afraid this "
"is the last we’ll be seeing of each other for some time."
msgstr ""
"Ah, ça va beaucoup mieux. Merci encore pour votre aide, vieil homme, mais je "
"crains que nous ne nous revoyions pas de sitôt."

#. [message]: speaker=Methor
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08x_Field_Hospital.cfg:114
#, fuzzy
msgid "Oh? You’ve been pulled back from the front?"
msgstr "Ah ? Vous avez été retiré du front ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Lionel
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08x_Field_Hospital.cfg:118
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Not quite. Remember Delfador’s prophecy? “Line of Kings”? “Sceptre of the "
"Wesfolk”?"
msgstr ""
"Pas exactement. Vous vous rappelez de la prophétie de Delfador ? « La lignée "
"des Rois » ? « Le Sceptre des Wesfolk » ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Lionel
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08x_Field_Hospital.cfg:122
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Well, Garard’s worried. Queen’s gossip is that one of the nobles knows where "
"the long-lost Sceptre of Fire is. I dunno if that’s true, but e’ryone knows "
"that the king should hold the Sceptre. If a noble did get their hands on it "
"they’d have a pretty strong claim to Garard’s throne."
msgstr ""
"Eh bien, Garard s’inquiète. Les commérages venant de la reine disent qu’un "
"des nobles sait où se trouve le Sceptre de Feu perdu depuis longtemps. Je ne "
"sais pas si c’est vrai, mais tout le monde sait que le roi devrait détenir "
"le Sceptre. Si un noble mettait la main dessus, il aurait une solide "
"revendication sur le trône de Garard."

#. [message]: speaker=Lionel
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08x_Field_Hospital.cfg:126
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The king’s sendin’ me and an entire company of Weldyn’s most finest on a "
"’grand journey’ into the wildlands to find the Sceptre first, and ensure he "
"stays firmly in power."
msgstr ""
"Le roi m’envoie, avec toute une compagnie des meilleurs soldats de Weldyn, "
"dans les terres sauvages pour trouver le Sceptre en premier et ainsi "
"consolider son pouvoir."

#. [message]: speaker=Methor
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08x_Field_Hospital.cfg:130
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Good gods, why now? Wesnoth is in enough trouble as it is, without worrying "
"about lost artifacts and suicide missions."
msgstr ""
"Grands dieux, pourquoi maintenant ? Wesnoth est déjà en assez mauvaise "
"posture comme ça, sans qu’on ait à s’inquiéter d’artefacts perdus et de "
"missions suicides."

#. [message]: speaker=Lionel
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08x_Field_Hospital.cfg:134
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You know how the king can be when he gets his mind set on somethin’. And if "
"someone really is trying to usurp the throne... Well, I only hope I can find "
"the Sceptre quickly, and resume my place at the king’s side."
msgstr ""
"Vous savez comment le roi peut être quand il se met quelque chose en tête… "
"Et si quelqu’un cherche réellement à usurper le trône… Eh bien, j’espère "
"mettre la main sur le Sceptre rapidement et retrouver ma place à ses côtés."

#. [message]: speaker=Methor
#. this mirrors Deoran's request to Delfador in S10x
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08x_Field_Hospital.cfg:145
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Lionel! You don’t... <b><i>have</i></b> to go, you know. You’re Garard’s top "
"general — if you refuse, I’m not sure there’s much he could do about it."
msgstr ""
"Lionel ! Vous n’…<b><i>êtes pas obligé</i></b> d’y aller, vous savez. Vous "
"êtes le meilleur général de Garard — si vous refusez, je ne suis pas sûr "
"qu’il puisse vraiment vous y contraindre."

#. [message]: speaker=Methor
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08x_Field_Hospital.cfg:149
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"And it would be for the king’s own good! Garard needs you <b><i>here</i></"
"b>, Lionel! Wesnoth needs you here."
msgstr ""
"Et ce serait pour le bien même du roi ! Garard a besoin de vous <b><i>ici</"
"i></b>, Lionel ! Wesnoth a besoin de vous ici."

#. [message]: speaker=Lionel
#. [message]: speaker=Omaranth
#. [message]: speaker=Aethyr
#. [message]: speaker=Asheviere
#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08x_Field_Hospital.cfg:153
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:123
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:294
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:727
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:277
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:333
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:401
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:298
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:950
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1460
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13x_The_King_is_Dead.cfg:196
msgid "..."
msgstr "…"

#. [message]: speaker=Lionel
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/08x_Field_Hospital.cfg:157
#, fuzzy
msgid "I’m loyal, Methor. Always have been, always will be."
msgstr "Je suis loyal, Methor. Je l’ai toujours été, et je le serai toujours."

#. [scenario]
#. [unit]
#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:11
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:786
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:311
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:398
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/utils/unified_characters.cfg:151
msgid "Omaranth"
msgstr "Omaranth"

#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:41
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:32
#, fuzzy
msgid "Omaranth’s Flight"
msgstr "Le vol d'Omaranth"

#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:58
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:55
#, fuzzy
msgid "Fauna"
msgstr "Faune"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:89
#, fuzzy
msgid "30 gold"
msgstr "30 pièces d'or"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:96
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Whoever destroyed this place did not care to loot it. We’ve gained 30 more "
"gold for our treasury."
msgstr ""
"Qui que ce soit qui ait détruit cet endroit, il ne s’est pas donné la peine "
"de le piller. Nous avons récupéré 30 pièces d’or de plus pour notre trésor."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#. $saurian_guide_name is a female saurian name generated with the default Wesnoth name generator
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:150
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"What ails you, $saurian_guide_name? I have trusted you thus far as a sign of "
"good faith — please don’t make me regret that decision."
msgstr ""
"Que t’arrive-t-il, $saurian_guide_name ? Je t’ai fait confiance jusqu’ici "
"comme gage de bonne foi — ne me fais pas regretter cette décision."

#. [message]: speaker=$saurian_guide_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:154
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Oh Great One, the other Great One livesss in thessse cold mountain "
"sssnowsss. But it is dangerousss! I am eldessst of my tribe... near "
"sssixteen years of age. Age hasss made me weak; too weak to travel thessse "
"landsss without help."
msgstr ""
"Ô Grand Être, l’autre Grand être vit dans cesss neigesss froidesss des "
"montagnes. Mais c’est dangereux ! Je sssuis la plus âgée de ma tribu… près "
"de sssseize ans. L’âge m’a affaiblie ; trop faible pour parcourir cesss "
"terres sssans aide."

#. [message]: speaker=$saurian_guide_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:158
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"But you are young! You are mighty! Your fire ssshall warm usss in the cold "
"and protect usss from the dangersss! Together, yesss, together we ssshall "
"reach the valley!"
msgstr ""
"Mais tu es jeune ! et plein de puissssance ! Ton feu nousss réchauffera dans "
"le froid et nousss protégera desss dangers ! Ensssemble, ouisss, ensssemble "
"nousss atteindrons la vallée !"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#. $saurian_guide_name will be a female saurian name generated with the default Wesnoth name generator
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:174
#, fuzzy
msgid "Move $saurian_guide_name to the marked hex"
msgstr "Déplacez $saurian_guide_name vers la case marquée."

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#. $saurian_guide_name will be a female saurian name generated with the default Wesnoth name generator
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:183
#, fuzzy
msgid "Death of $saurian_guide_name"
msgstr "Mort de $saurian_guide_name"

#. [note]
#. $saurian_guide_name will be a female saurian name generated with the default Wesnoth name generator
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:192
#, fuzzy
msgid "$saurian_guide_name will not follow you to the next scenario."
msgstr "$saurian_guide_name ne vous suivra pas au scénario suivant."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#. $saurian_guide_name will be a female saurian name generated with the default Wesnoth name generator
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:211
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"$saurian_guide_name, could we not have brought augurs along on this journey? "
"I’ve mastered many forms of magic, but the light of a healer is beyond my "
"reach."
msgstr ""
"« $saurian_guide_name, n’aurions-nous pas pu emmener des augures avec nous "
"pour ce voyage ? J’ai acquis la maîtrise de bien des formes de magie, mais "
"la lumière d’un guérisseur reste hors de ma portée. »"

#. [message]: speaker=$saurian_guide_id
#. the matriarch assumes both Delfador and the drake are female
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:216
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Oh Great One, you know it isss forbidden! The malesss are not permitted! "
"Only you and I; usss femalesss may look upon the other Great One; your "
"sssister, our massster, our god!"
msgstr ""
"Ô Grande élue, tu sssais que ccc’est interdit ! Les mâlesss ne sssont pas "
"autorisés ! Toi et moi sssseulement ; nous, les femellesss, pouvons "
"contempler l’autre Grande Élue ; ta sssœur, notre maîtresssse, notre "
"déesssse !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:220
#, fuzzy
msgid "Us females? Err, yes, that’s right."
msgstr "Nous, les femelles ? Euh… oui, c’est ça."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:239
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"So many bones! And they don’t look human... Is such death all work of your "
"great dragon?"
msgstr ""
"Tant d’os ! Et ils ne semblent pas humains… Toute cette mort est-elle "
"l’œuvre de ton grand dragon ?"

#. [message]: speaker=$saurian_guide_id
#. there were living drakes here only 20-30 years ago, but saurians have a very short lifespan.
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:244
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"No, this valley is cursssed... My grandmother usssed to sssay there were "
"once many powerful creaturesss in thisss place, but they were ssslain long "
"before I wasss hatched. Now only our Great One remainsss."
msgstr ""
"Non, cette vallée est maudite… Ma grand-mère disssait qu’autrefois, il y "
"avait de nombreuses créaturesss puissssantes en ce lieu, mais elles furent "
"tuéesss bien avant que je ne sois éclossse. Maintenant, seule notre Grande "
"Élue subsissste."

#. [message]: speaker=$saurian_guide_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:248
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"But once you find her, then there ssshall be two! Together the Great Onesss "
"will be unssstoppable!"
msgstr ""
"Mais une fois que tu la trouveras, alors il y en aura deux ! Ensssemble, les "
"Grandes Élues seront invinciblesss !"

#. [message]: speaker=$saurian_guide_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:260
#, fuzzy
msgid "Oh Great One! Sssave me!"
msgstr "« Ô Grand Être ! Sssauve-moi ! »"

#. [message]: speaker=$saurian_guide_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:276
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The sssnow, the windsss, it chillsss usss... Oh Great One, even with your "
"warmth, we cannot ssstay here long!"
msgstr ""
"La neige, les ventsss… ils nous saisisssent jusqu’aux os… Ô Grande Élue, "
"même avec ta chaleur, nous ne pourrons pas rester ici longtemps !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:280
#, fuzzy
msgid "We must keep moving."
msgstr "Il faut qu’on continue à avancer."

#. [message]: speaker=$saurian_guide_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:288
#, fuzzy
msgid "The cold chillsss me ssso! I cannot sssurvive much longer!"
msgstr ""
"Le froid… me glace jusqu’aux os ! Je ne peux plus tenir bien longtemps !"

#. [message]: speaker=$saurian_guide_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:296
#, fuzzy
msgid "Ssso... cccold... Oh Great One, I have failed you..."
msgstr "Si… froid… Ô Grand Être, je vous ai fait défaut…"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:343
#, fuzzy
msgid "Well?"
msgstr "Eh bien ?"

#. [message]: speaker=$saurian_guide_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:347
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Yesss, oh Great One, thisss is the place! Thisss is the lair of the other "
"Great One, your sssister, our massster, our god!"
msgstr ""
"Ouuui, ô Grand Être, c’est ici ! C’est la tanière de l’autre Grande élue, ta "
"ssssœur, notre maîtresse, notre déesse !"

#. [message]: speaker=$saurian_guide_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:355
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Sssimply continue down the valley, and you ssshall meet your sssissster! I "
"dare go no further. Oh massstersss, please forgive usss..."
msgstr ""
"Sssuivez tout sssimplement la vallée, et vous trouverez votre ssssœur ! Je "
"n'ose pas aller plus loin. Ô maîtressse, pardonnez‑nous…"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:474
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Hmph. What’s she so afraid of. Dragons are powerful, but hardly invulnerable."
msgstr ""
"Hm. De quoi a-t-elle donc si peur ? Les dragons sont puissants, mais pas "
"invulnérables."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:480
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The poets will sing my praises through the streets of Weldyn! After all, the "
"heroes of old used to slay dragons all the time."
msgstr ""
"Les poètes célébreront mes exploits dans chaque rue de Weldyn ! Après tout, "
"les héros d’antan tuaient des dragons à tout bout de champ."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:486
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Well, now that I think of it, I only remember reading about one single slain "
"dragon, many years ago."
msgstr ""
"Bon, en y réfléchissant, je ne me souviens d’avoir lu que l’histoire d’un "
"seul dragon tué, il y a de nombreuses années."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:492
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"And Prince Haldric did have a whole company of the Green Isle’s best knights "
"to help..."
msgstr ""
"Et le prince Haldric avait toute une compagnie des meilleurs chevaliers de "
"l’Île Verte pour l’aider…"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:498
#, fuzzy
msgid "Ah."
msgstr "Ah."

#. [message]: speaker=Omaranth
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:516
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"SOMETHING STIRS.\n"
"A HUMAN COMES."
msgstr ""
"QUELQUE CHOSE BOUGE.\n"
"UN HUMAIN ARRIVE."

#. [message]: speaker=Omaranth
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:523
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"IT IS FEEBLE.\n"
"IT IS WEAK.\n"
"IT WILL DIE."
msgstr ""
"IL EST FAIBLE.\n"
"IL EST VULNÉRABLE.\n"
"IL VA MOURIR."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:530
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"...wait a minute, that’s not a dragon, it’s merely a drake! The saurians "
"must have mistaken it for a true dragon on account of its fire breath."
msgstr ""
"…attends une minute, ce n’est pas un dragon, ce n’est qu’un dracan ! Les "
"sauriens ont dû le confondre avec un vrai dragon à cause de son souffle de "
"feu"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:534
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"So you are the villain behind all of this. You threaten my home and you "
"threaten my king — my friend."
msgstr ""
"Donc c’est toi le coupable derrière tout cela. Tu mets en danger ma demeure "
"et tu menaces mon roi, qui est aussi mon ami."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:545
#, fuzzy
msgid "Hey, get back here!"
msgstr "Hé, reviens ici !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:552
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"This drake is important — we cannot let it escape. My companions, I task you "
"to guard this cave entrance while I chase the drake inside. I know not why "
"it and the saurians that worship it are warring against Wesnoth, but I do "
"know they must be stopped."
msgstr ""
"Ce dracan est important — nous ne pouvons pas le laisser s’échapper. Mes "
"compagnons, je vous charge de garder l’entrée de cette caverne pendant que "
"je poursuis le dracan à l’intérieur. Je ne sais pas pourquoi lui et les "
"sauriens qui le vénèrent font la guerre à Wesnoth, mais je sais qu’il faut "
"les arrêter."

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:583
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You got it, boss. We’ll watch the cave entrance, and make sure you don’t get "
"trapped inside."
msgstr ""
"Bien reçu, patron. On gardera l’entrée de la caverne et on veillera à ce que "
"tu ne restes pas coincé dedans."

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:594
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Sounds like a pretty easy job. All we gots to do is wait ’round here for the "
"boss to come back out."
msgstr ""
"Ça n’a air d'être un boulot plutôt facile. Tout ce qu’on a à faire, c’est "
"attendre ici que le patron revienne."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:602
#, fuzzy
msgid "Relax. What could go wrong?"
msgstr "Détends-toi. Qu’est-ce qui pourrait mal tourner ?"

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:609
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:1082
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:1117
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"In this scenario $companion_name is your leader, and can recruit / recall."
msgstr ""
"Dans ce scénario, $companion_name est votre chef et peut recruter / rappeler."

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:741
#, fuzzy
msgid "Look out! One of them was lurking just inside the cave entrance!"
msgstr "Faites gaffe ! L’un d’eux rôdait juste à l’entrée de la caverne !"

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:752
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"That’s the last one ’o them, and with all the caves collapsed there won’t be "
"more! Nothing left to do but wait for Delfador to come back out, and "
"relax... for real this time. Great work everybody."
msgstr ""
"C’était le dernier d’entre eux, et avec toutes les cavernes effondrées, il "
"n’y en aura pas d’autres ! Plus qu’à attendre que Delfador revienne… et se "
"détendre… vraiment cette fois. Du bon boulot de tout le monde."

#. [message]: role=escort1
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:929
#, fuzzy
msgid "Brrr... It’s suddenly so c-c-cold..."
msgstr "Brrr… tout devient si f-f-froid d’un coup…"

#. [message]: id=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:961
#, fuzzy
msgid "Uhh, hello? Who’s there? Boss, is that you?"
msgstr "Euh… salut ? Qui est là ? Patron, c’est toi ?"

#. [message]: role=escort1
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:1015
#, fuzzy
msgid "Aaaah!"
msgstr "Aaaah!"

#. [message]: role=escort1
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:1028
#, fuzzy
msgid "Hell no! Curse it all, I didn’t sign up for fighting zombies!"
msgstr ""
"Mais pas question ! Bon sang, je ne me suis pas engagé pour combattre des "
"zombies !"

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:1032
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"C’mon everyone, grab your weapons and get ready. I’ve a feeling we’re about "
"to have the fight of our lives!"
msgstr ""
"Allez, tous à vos armes ! J’ai le pressentiment qu’on va livrer le combat de "
"notre vie !"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:1071
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:1103
#, fuzzy
msgid "Protect Delfador’s cave entrance until turns run out"
msgstr "Protégez l'entrée de la caverne de Delfador jusqu'à la fin des tours."

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:1075
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:1107
#, fuzzy
msgid "Delfador’s cave entrance is destroyed"
msgstr "L'entrée de la caverne de Delfador est détruite."

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:1098
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Look, a frozen cave, just like the one Delfador went down! I’ll bet these’re "
"where all the undead are climbing out of. Quick now, if we knock down the "
"entrance we can trap the zombies inside!"
msgstr ""
"Regardez, une caverne dans la glace, exactement comme celle où Delfador est "
"descendu ! Je parie que c’est de là que tous les morts-vivants sortent. "
"Vite, si on abat l’entrée, on peut piéger les zombies à l’intérieur !"

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:1114
#, fuzzy
msgid "Destroy hostile cave entrances to prevent enemies from emerging."
msgstr ""
"Détruisez les entrées des cavernes ennemies pour empêcher les ennemis d'en "
"sortir."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:1137
#, fuzzy
msgid "RraaaAAARRRGGG!"
msgstr "GrrrraaaAAARRRGGHH"

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:1165
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Ghost!! How’re we supposed to fight something our weapons can barely touch!?"
msgstr ""
"Un fantôme !! Comment est-ce qu’on est censés combattre quelque chose que "
"nos armes peuvent à peine atteindre ?"

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:1199
#, fuzzy
msgid "Wha— what’s happening!?"
msgstr "Qu-… qu’est-ce qui se passe !?"

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:1216
#, fuzzy
msgid "The undead have gone! Thank the gods! It’s finally over."
msgstr "Les morts-vivants ont disparu ! Dieu merci ! C’est enfin terminé."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:1220
#, fuzzy
msgid "I’m alive... I can’t believe it..."
msgstr "Je suis encore vivant…Je n’en reviens pas…"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:1221
#, fuzzy
msgid "female^I’m alive... I can’t believe it..."
msgstr "Je suis encore vivante…Je n’en reviens pas…"

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:1225
#, fuzzy
msgid "I think we won! ...but how?"
msgstr "On a l’air d’avoir gagné ! …mais comment est-ce possible ?"

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:1226
#, fuzzy
msgid "female^I think we won! ...but how?"
msgstr "Je crois qu'on a gagné ! ...mais comment ?"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:1256
#, fuzzy
msgid "The center crypt’s collapsing! We’ve failed!"
msgstr "La crypte centrale s'effondre ! Nous avons perdu !"

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/09_Omaranth.cfg:1260
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"We did our best, but the boss ain’t comin’ back out anytime soon. We’d "
"better scram back down south before the same happens to us."
msgstr ""
"On a fait de notre mieux, mais le patron n'est pas près de revenir. On "
"ferait mieux de filer au sud avant que la même chose ne nous arrive."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:4
#, fuzzy
msgid "Houses of the Dead"
msgstr "Les Demeures des Morts"

#. [message]
#. notice that appears at the beginning of the scenario if you select Brutal difficulty
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:93
#, fuzzy
msgid "Meanwhile..."
msgstr "Pendant ce temps-là…"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:119
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Stand and fight me, drake! You and your saurians have caused Wesnoth enough "
"harm. In the name of King Garard, your villainy ends here."
msgstr ""
"Fais face et affronte-moi, dracan ! Toi et tes sauriens avez déjà fait trop "
"de mal à Wesnoth. Au nom du roi Garard, ta perfidie s’arrête ici."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:130
#, fuzzy
msgid "...I suppose we’ll have to do this the hard way."
msgstr "…On dirait qu’il va falloir mener ça à la dure."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:138
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:329
#, fuzzy
msgid "Find Omaranth"
msgstr "Trouver Omaranth"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:205
#, fuzzy
msgid "A drakish tomb? This looks ominous..."
msgstr "Une sépulture dracane ? Ça ne présage rien de bon…"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:240
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"A ghost! Walking corpses are a great evil, but mastery over spirits is far "
"fouler still. Damned vessels, conscious but enslaved... yet where there are "
"enchantments, there are opportunities."
msgstr ""
"Un fantôme ! Les morts-vivants sont un grand mal, mais la maîtrise des "
"esprits est encore plus abominable. Vils réceptacles, conscients mais "
"asservis… pourtant là où il y a des enchantements, il y a des opportunités."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:250
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I must concentrate. The slightest mistake in the casting of this spell could "
"be fatal."
msgstr ""
"Je dois me concentrer. La moindre erreur en lançant ce sort pourrait être "
"fatale."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:266
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I call upon the name of An-Usrukhar the Great. I invoke the Mirror of "
"Evanescent Time!"
msgstr ""
"Au nom d’An-Usrukhar le Grand, j’invoque le Miroir du Temps Évanescent !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:273
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I challenge life against death! I invoke freedom against order! I wield "
"light against darkness!"
msgstr ""
"Je défie la vie contre la mort ! J’invoque la liberté contre l’ordre ! Je "
"brandis la lumière contre les ténèbres !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:280
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"May the coils of servitude be broken! Spirit of the damned, be freed from "
"your master."
msgstr ""
"Que les chaînes de la servitude soient brisées ! Esprit des damnés, sois "
"libéré de ton maître."

#. [message]: speaker=Aethyr
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:298
#, fuzzy
msgid "My mind... is my own..."
msgstr "Mon esprit… m’appartient…"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:302
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Speak, spectre! Tell me of this place. Where is the drake they call the "
"“Great One”?"
msgstr ""
"Parle, apparition ! Dis-moi tout sur cet endroit. Où se trouve le dracan "
"qu’on appelle le « Grand être» ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Aethyr
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:306
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I do not know. I know nothing of drakes. I am a man. My name is Aethyr... I "
"had almost forgotten. I died long ago, in a great battle..."
msgstr ""
"Je ne sais pas. Je ne sais rien au sujet des dracans. Je suis un homme. Mon "
"nom est Aethyr… je l’avais presque oublié. Je suis mort il y a bien "
"longtemps, lors d’une grande bataille…"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:308
#, fuzzy
msgid "Aethyr"
msgstr "Aethyr"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:311
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You’re the spirit of a human? How did you come to roam these drakish halls, "
"so far from the lands of men?"
msgstr ""
"Tu es l’esprit d’un humain ? Comment en es-tu venu à errer dans ces salles "
"dracanes, si loin des terres des hommes ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Aethyr
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:315
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Iliah-Malal brought me here. He made me promises of life renewed, but "
"instead bound me to his will. Perhaps Iliah-Malal will know of your drake."
msgstr ""
"Iliah-Malal m’a conduit ici. Il m’a fait la promesse d’une vie nouvelle, "
"mais il m’a asservi. Peut-être qu’Iliah-Malal en saurait plus sur ton dracan."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:319
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"A necromancer? Troubling. Yes, I should very much like to meet this Iliah-"
"Malal."
msgstr ""
"Un nécromancien ? C’est inquiétant. Oui, je voudrais vraiment rencontrer ce "
"Iliah-Malal."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:333
#, fuzzy
msgid "Find Iliah-Malal"
msgstr "Trouver Iliah-Malal"

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:340
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Delfador can capture hostile ghosts by moving adjacent to them, unless he is "
"polymorphed."
msgstr ""
"Delfador peut capturer les fantômes hostiles en se déplaçant à côté d’eux, "
"sauf s’il est polymorphé."

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:343
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:764
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:1105
#, fuzzy
msgid "Allied ghosts will not follow you to the next scenario."
msgstr "Les fantômes alliés ne vous suivront pas dans le scénario suivant."

#. [floating_text]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:378
#, fuzzy
msgid "Ghost Captured"
msgstr "Fantôme capturé"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:398
#, fuzzy
msgid "Sythan"
msgstr "Sythan"

#. [message]: speaker=Sythan
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:413
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I was once a great lord... I commanded armies! Iliah-Malal promised I would "
"lead again."
msgstr ""
"J’étais autrefois un grand seigneur… Je commandais des armées ! Iliah-Malal "
"m’avait promis que j’en dirigerais de nouveau."

#. [message]: speaker=Sythan
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:417
#, fuzzy
msgid "It was all a lie. I became only his slave."
msgstr "Tout cela n’était qu’un mensonge. Je ne suis devenu que son serviteur."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:426
#, fuzzy
msgid "Vellin Ka"
msgstr "Vellin Ka"

#. [message]: speaker=VellinKa
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:444
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Your banners were red.\n"
"Your spears were sharp.\n"
"Your hearts were cold."
msgstr ""
"Vos bannières étaient rouges.\n"
"Vos lances étaient acérées.\n"
"Vos cœurs étaient froids."

#. [message]: speaker=VellinKa
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:450
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Iliah-Malal led your army.\n"
"Iliah-Malal burned our Eyrie.\n"
"Iliah-Malal will die."
msgstr ""
"Iliah-Malal a mené votre armée.\n"
"Iliah-Malal a brûlé notre Aire.\n"
"Iliah-Malal mourra."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:456
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You’re a drake, and Iliah-Malal razed your home alongside... an army of "
"living men? And what of the drake called Omaranth; how did he survive if the "
"rest of you did not?"
msgstr ""
"Tu es un dracan, et Iliah-Malal a rasé ton foyer avec… une armée d’hommes "
"vivants ? Et qu’en est-il du dracan appelé Omaranth ; comment a-t-il survécu "
"si ce n’est pas le cas des autres ?"

#. [message]: speaker=VellinKa
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:460
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Omaranth was Dominant of our Flight.\n"
"Omaranth was strongest in our Eyrie.\n"
"Omaranth’s fate was not seen by I."
msgstr ""
"Omaranth était le Dominant de notre Vol.\n"
"Omaranth était le plus puissant de notre Aire.\n"
"Le destin d’Omaranth ne m’a pas été révélé."

#. [message]: id=$sun_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:493
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"A passage to the world above! Oh, how I long to go through and see the sun "
"again..."
msgstr ""
"Un passage vers le monde d'en haut ! Oh, comme je rêve de le traverser et de "
"revoir le soleil…"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:497
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Focus, spirit. This necromancer Iliah-Malal must have raised these corpses, "
"and now sends them against my allies on the surface. We must not abandon our "
"task here."
msgstr ""
"Concentrez-vous, esprit. Ce nécromancien, Iliah-Malal, a dû ressusciter ces "
"morts et il les envoie maintenant attaquer mes alliés à la surface. Nous ne "
"devons pas abandonner notre mission."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:510
msgid "Hagha-Tan"
msgstr "Hagha-Tan"

#. [message]: speaker=HaghaTan
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:525
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The chief called me to war... I knew the attack was risky, but I was "
"willing..."
msgstr ""
"Le chef m’a convoqué pour la guerre… Je savais que l’assaut serait "
"périlleux, mais j’étais volontaire…"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:529
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If you’re a recently-dead orc, does that mean you fell in battle against "
"Wesnoth? What can you tell me about your allies’ battle plans? Troop "
"movements?"
msgstr ""
"Si tu es un orc mort récemment, est-ce que cela veut dire que tu es tombé "
"face à Wesnoth ? Que sais-tu des plans de bataille de tes alliés ? Des "
"déplacements de troupes ?"

#. [message]: speaker=HaghaTan
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:534
#, fuzzy
msgid "You are no lord of mine, man of Wesnoth. I serve only my clan."
msgstr "Tu n’es pas mon seigneur, homme de Wesnoth. Je ne sers que mon clan."

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:544
msgid "Melinna"
msgstr "Melinna"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:558
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Are you a drake? Do you know anything about Omaranth, or this necromancer "
"Iliah-Malal?"
msgstr ""
"Es-tu un dracan ? Sais-tu quelque chose sur Omaranth, ou sur le nécromancien "
"Iliah-Malal ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Melinna
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:562
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I know only what I knew in life, Delfador. Yes, I recognize you... Garard’s "
"attack dog..."
msgstr ""
"Je ne sais que ce que je savais lorsque j’étais en vie, Delfador. Oui, je te "
"reconnais… le molosse de Garard…"

#. [message]: speaker=Melinna
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:566
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I was once a lady of the court. But the dead found me in the night. Now I "
"find myself here, in a form reflecting my fate. Who helped undead sneak into "
"Wesnoth? Why didn’t you keep us all safe..."
msgstr ""
"J’étais autrefois une dame de la cour. Mais les morts m’ont trouvée pendant "
"la nuit. Maintenant, je me retrouve ici, sous une forme qui reflète mon "
"destin. Qui a permis aux morts-vivants de s’infiltrer à Wesnoth ? Pourquoi "
"n’avez-vous pas tous veillé sur nous… ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:600
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"There is a gate here, sealed by runic energy. My magic should be able to "
"open it, but we must be prepared for whatever lies beyond."
msgstr ""
"l y a ici une porte, scellée par une énergie runique. Ma magie devrait "
"pouvoir l’ouvrir, mais il nous faut être prêts à affronter ce qui se cache "
"derrière."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:614
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Only Delfador has the power to open these gates... whatever lies beyond will "
"be most dangerous..."
msgstr ""
"Seul Delfador a le pouvoir d'ouvrir ces portes... ce qui se trouve au-delà "
"sera des plus dangereux..."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:634
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Whatever lurks behind this gate, it will be dangerous. I should make sure I "
"am prepared before I proceed."
msgstr ""
"Quoi qu’il y ait derrière cette porte, ce sera dangereux. Je dois m’assurer "
"d’être prêt avant de continuer."

#. [option]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:636
#, fuzzy
msgid "Open the gate"
msgstr "Ouvrir le portail"

#. [option]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:641
#, fuzzy
msgid "Wait"
msgstr "Attendre"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:731
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You! With so many undead about I was expecting to find the necromancer... I "
"don’t entirely understand what’s going on here, but I do know that you’re an "
"enemy of Wesnoth, and that’s good enough for me."
msgstr ""
"Toi ! Avec autant de morts-vivants, je m’attendais à trouver le "
"nécromancien… Je ne comprends pas tout ce qui se passe ici, mais je sais une "
"chose : tu es un ennemi de Wesnoth, et ça me suffit."

#. [message]: speaker=Omaranth
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:735
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"YOU INVADE MY HOME.\n"
"YOU SLAY MY SERVANTS.\n"
"YOU UNDERSTAND NOTHING."
msgstr ""
"TU ENVAHIS MA DEMEURE.\n"
"TU TUES MES SERVITEURS.\n"
"TU NE COMPRENDS RIEN."

#. [message]: speaker=Omaranth
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:741
#, fuzzy
msgid "NOW, YOU DIE."
msgstr "ET MAINTENANT, TU MEURS."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:757
#, fuzzy
msgid "Defeat Omaranth"
msgstr "Vaincre Omaranth"

#. [message]: speaker=Iliah-Malal
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:826
#, fuzzy
msgid "Ah ha, ha ha ha..."
msgstr "Ah ha, ha ha ha..."

#. [message]: speaker=Iliah-Malal
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:831
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Well fought, Delfador! They warned me you were dangerous, but to have found "
"me amidst all the vastness of the north — you have truly exceeded all "
"expectations!"
msgstr ""
"Bien joué, Delfador ! On m’avait prévenu que tu étais dangereux, mais te "
"trouver ici, au milieu de l’immensité du nord… tu as vraiment surpassé "
"toutes les attentes !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:835
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Now the story begins to make sense. The Omaranth I saw was never more than "
"an illusion. You are Iliah-Malal."
msgstr ""
"Maintenant, l’histoire commence à avoir du sens. L’Omaranth que j’ai vu "
"n’était jamais qu’une illusion. Tu es Iliah-Malal."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:839
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You wiped out this flight of drakes, and took the visage of their leader. "
"You led the saurians to join Clan Blackcrest, and you sent them to war "
"against Wesnoth. But why? How does all this fighting benefit a mage?"
msgstr ""
"Tu as exterminé ce vol de dracans et pris l’apparence de leur chef. Tu as "
"poussé les sauriens à s’allier au Clan Crêtes-noires, puis tu les as envoyés "
"en guerre contre Wesnoth. Mais pourquoi ? Quel avantage un mage tire-t-il de "
"toute cette violence ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Iliah-Malal
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:843
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"How does all <i><b>your</b></i> fighting benefit <i><b>you</b></i>? Decades "
"of war, and what has been gained? While you bleed for a failing country and "
"an aging king, your whole life is passing you by. You’re on the wrong side "
"of history, Delfador war-mage."
msgstr ""
"En quoi <i><b>tes</b></i> combats te profitent-ils <i><b>à toi</b></i> ? Des "
"décennies de guerre, et qu’as-tu gagné ? Pendant que tu te saignes pour un "
"pays moribond et un roi vieillissant, ta vie entière te file entre les "
"doigts. Tu es du mauvais côté de l’histoire, Delfador, mage de guerre."

#. [message]: speaker=Iliah-Malal
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:848
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"But you don’t have to be. Walk away! Stop wasting your life in service of an "
"old man, and finally act for yourself! Delfador, I have allies under whose "
"patronage you could live like a king, if you would only accept them!"
msgstr ""
"Mais tu n’as pas à l’être. Éloigne-toi ! Arrête de sacrifier ta vie pour un "
"vieux roi, et prends enfin tes propres décisions ! Delfador, j’ai des alliés "
"sous la protection desquels tu pourrais vivre comme un roi, si tu daignais "
"les rejoindre !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:852
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Like a king? I already serve a king, Iliah-Malal, and am well-loved for it. "
"Protecting Wesnoth is my <b><i>duty</i></b>. King Garard is my <b><i>friend</"
"i></b>. I hope you did not think to break me down so easily."
msgstr ""
"Comme un roi ? Je sers déjà un roi, Iliah-Malal, et je le fais avec loyauté. "
"Protéger Wesnoth est mon <b><i>devoir</i></b>. Le roi Garard est mon "
"<b><i>ami</i></b>. J’espère que tu ne pensais pas me faire fléchir si "
"facilement."

#. [message]: speaker=Iliah-Malal
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:856
#, fuzzy
msgid "Bah, remain a fool, then. You will not find me so easily broken either."
msgstr ""
"Bah, reste donc un imbécile. Tu ne me feras pas fléchir si facilement non "
"plus."

#. [message]: speaker=Iliah-Malal
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:897
#, fuzzy
msgid "Powers of darkness, confound my foes!"
msgstr "Puissances des ténèbres, confondez mes ennemis !"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:1098
#, fuzzy
msgid "Find and defeat Iliah-Malal, before his undead overwhelm you."
msgstr ""
"Trouver et vaincre Iliah-Malal, avant que ses morts-vivants ne vous "
"submergent."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:1120
#, fuzzy
msgid "Nice try, Delfador! You’ve only destroyed another illusion."
msgstr "Bien essayé, Delfador ! Tu n’as fait que détruire une autre illusion."

#. [message]: speaker=Iliah-Malal
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:1142
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"So you have found the real me. No matter. I shall have you yet, Delfador!"
msgstr ""
"Donc tu as découvert où je suis réellement. Peu importe. Je te vaincrai, "
"Delfador !"

#. [message]: speaker=Iliah-Malal
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:1157
#, fuzzy
msgid "Shadows consume you!"
msgstr "Les ombres vous consument !"

#. [message]: speaker=Iliah-Malal
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:1170
#, fuzzy
msgid "I should... have kept... my potion..."
msgstr "J’aurais dû… garder… ma potion…"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:1193
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Elende’s prophecy rings true once more: <i>“A figure of shadow cloaked in "
"the spirits of the dead”</i>... Good riddance. His meddling in life and "
"death has been the cause of great evil."
msgstr ""
"La prophétie d’Elende se vérifie encore une fois : <i>“Une silhouette "
"d’ombre, enveloppée des esprits des morts”</i>... Bon débarras. Ses "
"manipulations de la vie et de la mort ont été la source de grands maux."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:1210
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I am free... free! You have breathed into me a ravenousness for life anew, "
"life to drain from those who roam unfettered under the pale sun. Take us "
"into your service, Delfador; lead us to your foes! Lead us against the "
"living!"
msgstr ""
"Je suis libre… libre ! Tu m’as insufflé une soif de vie nouvelle, une vie à "
"drainer de ceux qui errent sans entraves sous le pâle soleil. Prends-nous à "
"ton service, Delfador ; mène-nous vers tes ennemis ! Mène-nous contre les "
"vivants !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:1214
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"No, no! Do not tempt me, I beg you, for that way madness lies... should I "
"ever start down that dark path I would never become free of it."
msgstr ""
"Non, non ! Ne me tente pas, je t’en supplie, car c’est là que la folie "
"réside… Si jamais je m’engageais sur ce chemin obscur, je ne pourrais jamais "
"m’en libérer."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:1218
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"No. But you have been of great service today, and for that you shall be "
"rewarded with peace."
msgstr ""
"Non. Mais ta contribution a été précieuse aujourd’hui, et pour cela, tu "
"recevras la paix en guise de récompense."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:1232
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Return to your land of calm and quiet, and trouble the living no longer. I "
"shall save my country without your help."
msgstr ""
"Retourne dans ton pays de calme et de silence, et ne trouble plus les "
"vivants. Je sauverai mon pays sans ton aide."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:1257
#, fuzzy
msgid "From the dead I came, and to the dead I return..."
msgstr "Je suis venu d'entre les morts, et je retourne aux morts..."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:1258
#, fuzzy
msgid "Rock and dust, bone and stone..."
msgstr "Roche et poussière, os et pierre…"

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:1259
#, fuzzy
msgid "Avenge my flight..."
msgstr "Venge mon vol…"

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:1260
#, fuzzy
msgid "Good luck, Delfador... Don’t trust anyone..."
msgstr "Bonne chance, Delfador… Ne fais confiance à personne…"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#. Delfador has just killed an enemy ghost. That's not a good thing - if he moves next to hostile ghosts without killing them, he can take control of them.
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10_Houses_of_the_Dead.cfg:1271
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"That one has returned to the land of the dead. Maybe I could have captured "
"it, if only I’d had a chance to try."
msgstr ""
"Celui-là est retourné au royaume des morts. J'aurais peut-être pu le "
"capturer, si seulement j'en avais eu l'occasion."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10x_Elensefar_Outskirts.cfg:4
#, fuzzy
msgid "Elensefar Outskirts"
msgstr "Environs d’Elensefar"

#. [message]: speaker=Maddock
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10x_Elensefar_Outskirts.cfg:97
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The answer is no. Garard, Elensefar has no interest in joining your little "
"war-clique. You’ve already stirred up enough trouble; trade up the river is "
"failing, and goblins are once again raiding my northern border."
msgstr ""
"La réponse est non. Garard, Elensefar n’a aucun intérêt à rejoindre ton "
"petit clan de guerre. Tu as déjà semé assez de chaos ; le commerce sur le "
"fleuve est en déclin, et les gobelins attaquent à nouveau ma frontière "
"septentrionale."

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10x_Elensefar_Outskirts.cfg:101
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"All the more reason to join forces and wipe the orcs out! Think how much "
"territory we could command if the Northlands were fully open to human "
"settlement."
msgstr ""
"C’est encore une raison de plus pour unir nos forces et éliminer les orcs ! "
"Pense à tout le territoire que nous pourrions contrôler si les Terres du "
"Nord étaient entièrement ouvertes à la colonisation."

#. [message]: speaker=Maddock
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10x_Elensefar_Outskirts.cfg:105
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If you were <i>winning</i>, certainly, but then we wouldn’t be speaking "
"together here, would we? You’ve never been one for sharing the spoils."
msgstr ""
"Si tu étais en train de <i>gagner</i>, bien sûr, mais dans ce cas, nous ne "
"serions pas en train de discuter ici, n'est-ce pas ? Tu n’as jamais été du "
"genre à partager les dépouilles."

#. [message]: speaker=Maddock
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10x_Elensefar_Outskirts.cfg:109
#, fuzzy
msgid "Now if you’ll excuse me, warmonger, I have a city to govern."
msgstr "Si tu veux bien m'excuser, va-t-en guerre, j’ai une ville à gouverner."

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10x_Elensefar_Outskirts.cfg:122
#, fuzzy
msgid "Damn his cowardice! Still no word from Lionel?"
msgstr "Maudit soit sa lâcheté ! Toujours aucune nouvelle de Lionel ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10x_Elensefar_Outskirts.cfg:126
#, fuzzy
msgid "(stares)"
msgstr "(fixe en silence)"

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10x_Elensefar_Outskirts.cfg:130
#, fuzzy
msgid "Speak UP, boy! I raised you to be a killer, not a coward!"
msgstr "PARLE, mon garçon ! Je t’ai élevé pour être un tueur, pas un poltron !"

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10x_Elensefar_Outskirts.cfg:134
#, fuzzy
msgid "You hardly raised me at all..."
msgstr "Tu ne m’as pas vraiment élevé…"

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10x_Elensefar_Outskirts.cfg:138
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Oh, confound it. Why did I let those infernal rumors convince me to send "
"away my best general and most loyal soldiers?\n"
"\n"
"Lionel is missing in action, Arand becomes more paranoid by the day, and you "
"still speak softer than a mouse. This is war — Wesnoth needs a warrior "
"prince."
msgstr ""
"Oh, maudit soit cela. Pourquoi ai-je laissé ces rumeurs infernales me "
"convaincre d’envoyer mon meilleur général et mes soldats les plus loyaux ?\n"
"\n"
"Lionel est porté disparu, Arand devient de plus en plus paranoïaque chaque "
"jour, et toi, tu parles toujours plus doucement qu’une souris. C’est la "
"guerre — Wesnoth a besoin d’un prince guerrier."

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10x_Elensefar_Outskirts.cfg:144
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Even reliable Delfador took off months ago on some wild goose chase in the "
"Northlands. Some days it feels like the whole world is moving against me... "
"perhaps it is an omen of things to come."
msgstr ""
"Même Delfador, sur qui on peut toujours compter normalement, est parti "
"depuis des mois à la recherche de je ne sais quoi dans les Terres du Nord. "
"Certains jours, j’ai l’impression que le monde entier se retourne contre "
"moi… peut-être est-ce un présage de ce qui nous attend."

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10x_Elensefar_Outskirts.cfg:151
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The coward’s option once more rears its ugly head. Negotiate, capitulate; "
"yield the border to the butchers. Give unto the orcs their pound of flesh."
msgstr ""
"Une fois de plus, la voie de la lâcheté refait surface. Négocier, "
"capituler ; céder la frontière aux bouchers. Donner aux orcs leur livre de "
"chair."

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10x_Elensefar_Outskirts.cfg:155
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"How many would die? How many have already died to this problem of my own "
"making? I can already feel the kings of old judging me in my failure, my "
"squandering of everything they fought so hard to build..."
msgstr ""
"Combien vont mourir ? Combien sont déjà morts à cause de ce problème que "
"j'ai causé moi-même ? Je ressens déjà le poids du jugement des rois "
"d'autrefois, qui me condamnent pour mon échec, pour avoir gâché tout ce "
"qu'ils ont construit avec tant de sacrifice..."

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10x_Elensefar_Outskirts.cfg:160
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"No. I will not go down in history as a failed king; a weakling, a coward "
"powerless to protect his people against the savages beyond. I have chosen "
"the path of war, and I will see it through to its bloody end."
msgstr ""
"Non. Je ne resterai pas dans l'Histoire comme un roi défaillant ; un faible, "
"un lâche, impuissant à protéger son peuple contre les sauvages de l'autre "
"côté. J'ai choisi la voie de la guerre, et je la suivrai jusqu'à son "
"sanglant dénouement."

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/10x_Elensefar_Outskirts.cfg:165
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Riders, summon the reserves. Empty Halstead! Empty Weldyn! I want every "
"child old enough to walk and every elder young enough to stand!\n"
"\n"
"In two weeks time we march across the ford and assault the Blackcrest war-"
"camp. Come hell or high water, we will yet have our victory."
msgstr ""
"Cavaliers, rassemblez les réserves. Videz Halstead ! Videz Weldyn ! Je veux "
"que chaque enfant capable de marcher et que chaque vieillard encore assez "
"fort pour se tenir debout soient prêts !\n"
"\n"
"Dans deux semaines, nous franchirons le gué et attaquerons le camp des "
"Crêtes-noires. Qu'il pleuve ou qu'il vente, nous aurons notre victoire."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:11
msgid "Galcadar"
msgstr "Galcadar"

#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:47
#, fuzzy
msgid "Saurian Defectors"
msgstr "Déserteurs sauriens"

#. [side]
#. [unit]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:162
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1127
#, fuzzy
msgid "Chief Ghuvog"
msgstr "Chef Ghuvog"

#. [message]: speaker=Drakefador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:317
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Saurians of Saurgrath! It is I, your Great One, bringing an even greater "
"warning!"
msgstr ""
"Sauriens de Saurgrath ! C'est moi, votre Grand Être et je viens vous "
"délivrer un avertissement d'une importance encore plus grande !"

#. [message]: speaker=Drakefador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:321
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"These orcs have, umm, conspired to betray you! You must strike first and "
"kill them all — now hear me and obey!"
msgstr ""
"Ces orcs ont, euh, conspiré pour vous trahir ! Vous devez les frapper en "
"premier et les tuer tous — écoutez-moi et obéissez !"

#. [message]: speaker=defector4
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:326
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Can it be? The Great One ssspeaksss to usss! I am not worthy! I am blessed "
"to hear your great voice, unusssual though it may be!"
msgstr ""
"Essst-ce possible ? Le Grand Être nous parle ! Je n’en suis pas digne ! Je "
"sssuis béni d'entendre votre grande voix, bien que sssi… particulière !"

#. [message]: speaker=defector3
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:334
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Yesss, the great fiery one has sssaved usss! If the orcsss will betray us, "
"then we mussst ssstrike firssst!"
msgstr ""
"Sssi, le grand Être ardent nous a sssauvés ! Sssi les orcs veulent nous "
"trahir, alors nous devons frapper les premiers !"

#. [message]: speaker=defector2
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:338
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"...caution, caution, ssomething isss not right! Where are the ssseven "
"matriarchsss? Why does the Great One ssspeak ssso nasssally?"
msgstr ""
"...Attention, attention, quelque chose cloche ! Où sont les sssept "
"matriarches ? Pourquoi le Grand Être parle-t-il d'une voix si nasillarde ?"

#. [message]: speaker=defector3
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:343
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Do you not sssee her majesssty? It isss not our place to quessstion the "
"great fiery one!"
msgstr ""
"Ne voyez-vous pas sssa majesté ? Ce n'est pas à nous de défier le grand Être "
"de feu !"

#. [message]: speaker=Ghuvog
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:347
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Shut it, all of you! I don’t know why any of youse care what some off-brand "
"dragon says, but don’t forget that you lizards made a deal to fight with us "
"against Wesnoth. Even paid <i>us</i> for the privilege, you dumb little "
"worms!\n"
"\n"
"Now form up and get in line, before I have to beat some discipline into you!"
msgstr ""
"Fermez-la, tous autant que vous êtes ! Je ne sais pas pourquoi vous vous "
"souciez de ce que dit ce dragon de pacotille, mais n'oubliez pas que vous, "
"les lézards, avez conclu un marché pour combattre à nos côtés contre "
"Wesnoth. Vous nous avez même payé <i>pour</i> ce privilège, espèce de petits "
"vers stupides !\n"
"\n"
"Maintenant en formation et mettez-vous en ligne, avant que je ne sois obligé "
"de vous inculquer un peu de discipline !"

#. [message]: speaker=defector1
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:357
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You insssult usss! Worssse, you dare insssult the Great One! Curssses upon "
"you, cursses upon you! We ssshall fight you, we mussst fight you!"
msgstr ""
"Tu nous insssultes ! Pire encore, tu oses insssulter le Grand Être ! "
"Malédictions sssur toi, malédictions sssur toi ! Nous allons te combattre, "
"nous devons te combattre !"

#. [message]: speaker=defector3
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:365
#, fuzzy
msgid "Yesss, we mussst fight! Fight the orcsss!"
msgstr "Ouissse, nous devons combattre ! Combattre les orcs !"

#. [message]: speaker=Ghuvog
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:369
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Oh yeah? Try me, you filthy sacks of lizard slime; I’ll teach youse your "
"proper place! To arms, Blackcrests!!"
msgstr ""
"Oh ouais ? Essayez toujours, bande de sacs de bave de lézard ! Je vais vous "
"apprendre où est votre place ! Aux armes, les Crêtes-noires !!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:441
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Wesnoth’s foes are thrown into chaos! Iliah-Malal’s illusion magic has done "
"much harm. In my hands, perhaps it can do some good."
msgstr ""
"Les ennemis de Wesnoth sont plongés dans le chaos ! La magie d'illusion "
"d'Iliah-Malal a causé bien des ravages. Entre mes mains, peut-être pourra-t-"
"elle aboutir à quelque chose de bien."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:445
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"This is the great western horde — these tents have been a staging ground for "
"every Blackcrest attack on Wesnoth since they first entered the war, so many "
"years ago."
msgstr ""
"Voici la grande horde occidentale — ces tentes ont servi de point de "
"rassemblement pour chaque attaque des Crêtes-noires contre Wesnoth depuis "
"leur entrée en guerre, il y a de nombreuses d'années."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:449
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Every time I tried to lead soldiers across the river, it was these "
"fortifications that pushed me back. ’tis a funny feeling to finally see them "
"from the north side."
msgstr ""
"Chaque fois que j'ai voulu faire traverser des soldats, ce sont ces "
"fortifications qui m'ont forcé à reculer. Ça fait un drôle d’effet de les "
"voir enfin du côté nord."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:453
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"But more importantly, this is where the Blackcrest war-chief commands his "
"clan."
msgstr ""
"Mais surtout, c'est d’ici que le chef de guerre des Crêtes-noires commande "
"son clan."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:459
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"With most of the saurians defecting, this is our chance to kill the "
"Blackcrest chief and break their grip on the Abez once and for all. It’s all "
"led up to this! We can end things here and now!"
msgstr ""
"La plupart des sauriens ayant fait défection, nous avons la possibilité "
"d'éliminer le chef des Crêtes-noires et de briser définitivement leur "
"contrôle sur le gué. Tout converge vers cette occasion ! Nous pouvons en "
"finir ici et maintenant !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:463
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"For the sake of all Wesnoth, for the sake of King Garard, we cannot fail."
msgstr ""
"Pour le bien de tout Wesnoth, pour le bien du roi Garard, nous ne devons pas "
"échouer."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:472
#, fuzzy
msgid "Defeat Ghuvog, the Blackcrest war-chief"
msgstr "Vaincre Ghuvog, le chef de guerre des Crêtes-noires"

#. [objective]: condition=lose
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:490
#, fuzzy
msgid "Death of Garard"
msgstr "Mort de Garard"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#. in this string, $companion_name is female (probably "Lynyan")
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:517
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"female^Are you certain you’re prepared for this fight, $companion_name? "
"You’re an outlaw, not a soldier, and your posse has already bled more than I "
"paid you for. I shan’t lie and say your help is unneeded, but neither should "
"I take it for granted."
msgstr ""
"Es-tu bien sûr d'être prête pour ce combat, $companion_name ? Tu es une hors-"
"la-loi, pas un soldat, et ta bande a déjà versé son sang bien plus que ce "
"que je t'ai payé. Je ne vais pas mentir en disant que ton aide n'est pas "
"nécessaire, mais je ne devrais pas non plus la considérer comme acquise."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#. in this string, $companion_name is male
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:523
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Are you certain you’re prepared for this fight, $companion_name? You’re an "
"outlaw, not a soldier, and your posse has already bled more than I paid you "
"for. I shan’t lie and say your help is unneeded, but neither should I take "
"it for granted."
msgstr ""
"Es-tu bien sûr d'être prêt pour ce combat, $companion_name ? Tu es un hors-"
"la-loi, pas un soldat, et ta bande a déjà versé son sang bien plus que ce "
"que je t'ai payé. Je ne vais pas mentir en disant que ton aide n'est pas "
"nécessaire, mais je ne devrais pas non plus la considérer comme acquise."

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:528
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"...fighting a whole orcish army is a bit more than I signed on for, but you "
"say this is important and I trust you. I’m ready for this if you are."
msgstr ""
"... Combattre une armée entière d'orcs, c'est bien plus que ce pour quoi je "
"me suis engagé, mais si tu dis que c'est important, comme j'ai confiance en "
"toi. Je me tiens prêt à y faire face, si tu l'es aussi."

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:529
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"female^...fighting a whole orcish army is a bit more than I signed on for, "
"but you say this is important and I trust you. I’m ready for this if you are."
msgstr ""
"... Combattre une armée entière d'orcs, c'est bien plus que ce pour quoi je "
"me suis engagé, mais si tu dis que c'est important, comme j'ai confiance en "
"toi. Je suis prête à y faire face, si tu l'es aussi."

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:535
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"And hey, if nothing else, at least I’ve got to admit that adventuring with "
"you pays a lot better than skulkin’ around picking pockets."
msgstr ""
"Et, pour être honnête, au moins je dois admettre que l'aventure à tes côtés "
"ça paye beaucoup mieux que de traîner dans le coin pour faire les poches."

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:536
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"female^And hey, if nothing else, at least I’ve got to admit that adventuring "
"with you pays a lot better than skulkin’ around picking pockets."
msgstr ""
"Et, pour être honnête, au moins je dois admettre que l'aventure à tes côtés "
"ça paye beaucoup mieux que de traîner dans le coin pour faire les poches."

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:542
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"And hey, if nothing else, at least I’ve got to admit that adventuring with "
"you pays a lot better than runnin’ errands for some thug."
msgstr ""
"Et puis, au moins, je dois admettre que partir à l'aventure avec toi "
"rapporte bien plus que de faire des courses au profit d'un vaurien."

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:543
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"female^And hey, if nothing else, at least I’ve got to admit that adventuring "
"with you pays a lot better than runnin’ errands for some thug."
msgstr ""
"Et puis, au moins, je dois admettre que partir à l'aventure avec toi "
"rapporte bien plus que de faire des courses au profit d'un vaurien."

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:549
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"And hey, if nothing else, at least I’ve got to admit that adventuring with "
"you pays a lot better than castin’ cantrips for some thug."
msgstr ""
"Et puis, au moins, je dois admettre que partir à l'aventure avec toi "
"rapporte bien plus que de jeter des sorts au profit d'un vaurien."

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:550
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"female^And hey, if nothing else, at least I’ve got to admit that adventuring "
"with you pays a lot better than castin’ cantrips for some thug."
msgstr ""
"Et puis, au moins, je dois admettre que partir à l'aventure avec toi "
"rapporte bien plus que de jeter des sorts au profit d'un vaurien."

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:556
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"And hey, if nothing else, at least I’ve got to admit that adventuring with "
"you pays a lot better than muckin’ around in swamps all night."
msgstr ""
"Et puis, faut bien l’avouer, l’aventure avec toi rapporte bien plus que "
"traîner dans les marais toute la nuit."

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:557
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"female^And hey, if nothing else, at least I’ve got to admit that adventuring "
"with you pays a lot better than muckin’ around in swamps all night."
msgstr ""
"Et puis, faut bien l’avouer, l’aventure avec toi rapporte bien plus que "
"traîner dans les marais toute la nuit."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:570
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Welcome to the Ford of Abez\n"
"South: Tath\n"
"North:<span strikethrough='true'> Dwarven Doors </span>"
msgstr ""
"Bienvenue au Gué d'Abez\n"
"Sud : Tath\n"
"Nord : Portes naines"

#. [message]: speaker=$unit.id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:588
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I sssurrender, I sssurrender! Chief Ghuvog is the true Great One; my "
"allegiance isss only to you, great chief! Pleassse, ssspare me and my kin!"
msgstr ""
"Je me rends, je me rends ! Le chef Ghuvog est le véritable Grand Être ; ma "
"loyauté est toute pour toi, grand chef ! S'il te plaît, épargne-moi, ainsi "
"que ma tribu !"

#. [message]: speaker=Ghuvog
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:597
#, fuzzy
msgid "Now that’s more like it! Fall into line and get ready to fight."
msgstr ""
"Voilà qui est mieux ! Mettez-vous en ligne et préparez-vous à combattre."

#. [message]: speaker=$unit.id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:611
#, fuzzy
msgid "You betray the Great One... the stars shall bring your doom..."
msgstr "Tu as trahis le Grand Être... les étoiles vont t'amener à ta perte..."

#. [message]: speaker=Ghuvog
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:624
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Graahh!! Get out of here, you stinking pink-skins! Now is not a good time!"
msgstr ""
"Graahh !! Dégagez de là, sales blancs-becs ! Ce n'est vraiment pas le "
"moment !"

#. [message]: speaker=Ghuvog
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:637
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Hey, lay off my Shamans! Do you have any idea how hard it is to find those!?"
msgstr ""
"Hé, touche pas à mes Chamanes ! Tu sais à quel point c’est difficile d’en "
"dénicher ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Ghuvog
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:649
#, fuzzy
msgid "Out of my face, worms!"
msgstr "Hors de ma vue, vermissaux !"

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#. yes yes, Delfador probably hasn't attacked any orcs by now (and he might not be using fire). But it's a cool line.
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:714
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Ah-ha! I’d recognize that smell of burning orc-flesh anywhere – Delfador has "
"returned!"
msgstr ""
"Ah-ha ! Je reconnaîtrais cette odeur de chair d'orc brûlée à des lieues de "
"distance – Delfador est de retour !"

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:723
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"This is the chance I’ve been waiting for; my golden, desperate opportunity "
"to crush the orcs now and forever! Once more unto the breach – captain, "
"break me an opening through the enemy lines!"
msgstr ""
"C’est l’occasion que j’attendais depuis si longtemps ; une chance en or, "
"désespérée, d'écraser les orcs une bonne fois pour toutes! Une dernière "
"charge dans la brèche – capitaine, ouvre-moi un passage dans les rangs "
"ennemis !"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:797
#, fuzzy
msgid "You heard the king; form up, and prepare to storm the front!"
msgstr ""
"Vous avez entendu le roi ; formez les rangs et préparez-vous à monter à "
"l’assaut !"

#. [object]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:892
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Deoran has rejoined Delfador’s party, and you have gained 100 extra gold!"
msgstr ""
"Deoran a réintégré les rangs de Delfador, et vous obtenez 100 pièces d'or "
"supplémentaires !"

#. [object]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:894
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"For the remainder of this campaign, Deoran is a leader — he can recruit "
"fresh royal soldiers (Spearmen, Bowmen, etc.) while standing on his keep."
msgstr ""
"Pour le reste de cette campagne, Deoran est un chef de guerre – il peut "
"recruter de nouveaux soldats royaux (porte-lance, archers, etc.) tant qu'il "
"se trouve sur son donjon."

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:923
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"For Wesnoth! For victory! By battle and blood, for fury and flame, and the "
"triumph of my people!"
msgstr ""
"Pour Wesnoth ! Pour la victoire ! Par le combat et le sang, par la fureur et "
"les flammes, et le triomphe de mon peuple !"

#. [message]: speaker=Ghuvog
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:947
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"All right, all right, I know when I’m beat! Let’s not be hasty, there’s no "
"need for more death and violence. <span size='x-small'>Against me, anyhow. "
"Nasty pink-skin whelps.</span>"
msgstr ""
"C'est Bon, c'est bon, je reconnais ma défaite ! Ne soyons pas trop "
"impulsifs, on n'a pas besoin de plus de morts et de violence. <span size='x-"
"small'>Contre moi, en tout cas. Sales rejetons de blancs-becs .</span>"

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:958
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Watch your tongue, vermin! I am no ’whelp’, but King Garard of Wesnoth, "
"second of his name!\n"
"\n"
"And in that name, for the Kingdom of Wesnoth, I hereby annex these lands "
"from the Great River in the south to the foothills of the Heart Mountains in "
"the north! You orcs shall fall beneath our swords as wheat before the scythe!"
msgstr ""
"Surveille ta langue, paltoquet ! Je ne suis pas un « rejeton », mais le roi "
"Garard de Wesnoth, second du nom !\n"
"Et en ce nom, pour le royaume de Wesnoth, je décrète l'annexion de ces "
"terres, de la Grande Rivière au sud jusqu'aux contreforts des Montagnes du "
"Cœur au nord ! Vous, orcs, tomberez sous nos épées comme le blé sous la "
"faux !"

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:964
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"...but I am no fool. Wesnoth is tired of war, and your lord Garard is "
"nothing if not merciful. I will spare your life and the life of your "
"warriors, on one condition.\n"
"\n"
"You must hereby swear an oath to gather both your clan from here, and Clan "
"Whitefang from the hills around Fort Garard. You shall leave these lands and "
"never return so long as I draw breath, on pain of death!"
msgstr ""
".. mais je ne suis pas un aliboron. Wesnoth en a assez de la guerre, et "
"votre seigneur Garard est tout sauf sans pitié. Je vous épargnerai la vie, "
"ainsi que celle de vos guerriers, à une condition.\n"
"\n"
"Vous devrez prêter serment de regrouper votre clan ainsi que le Clan Crocs-"
"blancs. Vous quitterez ces terres et ne reviendrez jamais tant que je serai "
"en vie, sous peine de mort !"

#. [message]: speaker=Ghuvog
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:970
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Yeah yeah yeah, whatever you say. We was just leaving; isn’t that right, "
"boys? <span size='x-small'>Nasty filthy pink-skins.</span>"
msgstr ""
"Ouais, ouais, ouais, comme tu veux. On partait de toute façon, pas vrai les "
"gars ?<span size='x-small'> Sales blancs-becs immondes</span>"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:987
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"After all this time... Wesnoth is finally at peace. It is as if a veil of "
"shadows has been lifted from upon my eyes!"
msgstr ""
"Après tout ce temps... Wesnoth est enfin en paix. On dirait qu'un voile de "
"ténèbres s'est retiré de devant mes yeux !"

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:991
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Delfador, you rascal, you’ve truly outdone yourself this time. They tell me "
"how you turned the saurians against the orcs, sowed chaos from behind; truly "
"incredible!"
msgstr ""
"Delfador, espèce de filou, tu t'es vraiment surpassé cette fois-ci. On m'a "
"raconté comment tu as retourné les sauriens contre les orcs, semé le chaos "
"par derrière ; c'est vraiment incroyable !"

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:995
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Delfador the “Great One”, hah! Now that’s the stuff legends are made of. So "
"legendary, in fact..."
msgstr ""
"Delfador le « Grand », ha ! Voilà de quoi forger une légende. Une légende à "
"proprement parler…"

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:1005
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"“The Great” you were called by the enemy, and “The Great” you shall be "
"called until the end of your days. Kneel, Delfador, war-mage of Wesnoth. And "
"rise, “Delfador the Great”, High Advisor to the Crown!"
msgstr ""
"Tu étais appelé « Le Grand » par l'ennemi, et tu seras appelé « Le Grand » "
"jusqu'à la fin de tes jours. Agenouille-toi, Delfador, mage de guerre de "
"Wesnoth. Et relève-toi, « Delfador le Grand », Haut Conseiller de la "
"Couronne !"

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:1021
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Now come, let us celebrate my— our— ...all right, <i><b>your</b></i> "
"success! Victory! Victory! Victory by the name of Delfador!!"
msgstr ""
"Allez, célébrons mon… notre… … d’accord, votre… succès ! Victoire ! "
"Victoire ! Victoire au nom de Delfador !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:1048
#, fuzzy
msgid "Huh."
msgstr "Hein."

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:1053
#, fuzzy
msgid "Whaddid you say, boss?"
msgstr "Qu'avez-vous dit, patron ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:1057
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Oh, nothing. I feel like something bad normally happens if we take this long "
"to finish a battle, but right now everything seems fine."
msgstr ""
"Oh, rien. J'ai l'impression que d'habitude, il se passe quelque chose de "
"grave si on met autant de temps à terminer une bataille, mais pour "
"l'instant, tout semble aller bien."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11_Clan_Blackcrest.cfg:1061
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"We’re <i>definitely not</i> missing out on significant events happening "
"elsewhere... events that we really should have been present for..."
msgstr ""
"Nous ne manquons absolument pas d'événements importants qui se déroulent "
"ailleurs... des événements auxquels nous aurions vraiment dû assister..."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:4
#, fuzzy
msgid "Revelry"
msgstr "Festivités"

#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:22
msgid "Moreth"
msgstr "Moreth"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:119
#, fuzzy
msgid "Three cheers for Delfador, hero of the Abez!"
msgstr "Trois ovations pour Delfador, le héros d'Abez !"

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:123
#, fuzzy
msgid "Three cheers— three cheers for Delfador the Great! Hurrah!"
msgstr ""
"Trois acclamations— trois acclamations pour Delfador le Grand ! Hourra !"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:129
#, fuzzy
msgid "Hurrah for Delfador!"
msgstr "Hourra pour Delfador!"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:136
#, fuzzy
msgid "Hooray for Delfador!"
msgstr "Vive Delfador !"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:143
#, fuzzy
msgid "Hurrah for Del— *hic* Delfador!"
msgstr "Hourra pour Del— *hic* Delfador!"

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:152
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Oh ho, someone fetch me more wine! The night’s still young; I’m ready for a "
"proper CELEBRATION!!"
msgstr ""
"Oh ho, que l’on aille me chercher du vin ! La nuit n’est pas encore finie ; "
"je suis prêt à fêter comme il se doit !!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:156
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I started as an inglorious apprentice, without even a name to call my own. "
"And now I have saved Wesnoth from war, and in the process become the king’s "
"most trusted advisor! Truly, this is more than I could have ever hoped for."
msgstr ""
"J'ai commencé comme un apprenti sans grande réputation, sans même un nom à "
"moi. Et maintenant, j'ai sauvé Wesnoth de la guerre, et en chemin, je suis "
"devenu le conseiller le plus digne de confiance du roi ! Vraiment, cela "
"dépasse tout ce que j'aurais pu espérer."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:160
#, fuzzy
msgid "I’m giddy with joy... or perhaps ’tis also the wine, heh."
msgstr ""
"Je suis fou de joie... ou peut-être que c’est un peu le vin aussi, héhé."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:164
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"My friend, you deserve it. Without their saurian allies Clan Blackcrest is "
"on the run, and Clan Whitefang is falling back out of the eastern hills."
msgstr ""
"Mon ami, tu le mérites. Sans leurs alliés saurien, le Clan Crêtes-noires est "
"en déroute, et le Clan Crocs-blancs se retire des collines de l'est."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:168
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"At long last lift the shadows of war; the realm is finally at peace. "
"Perchance the coming days will bring laughter to the streets of Weldyn once "
"again."
msgstr ""
"Enfin, les ombres de la guerre se dissipent ; le royaume est enfin en paix. "
"Peut-être que les jours à venir ramèneront des rires dans les rues de Weldyn."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:172
#, fuzzy
msgid "For the first time in a long time, all is finally well with the world."
msgstr ""
"Pour la première fois depuis longtemps, tout va enfin bien dans ce monde."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:218
#, fuzzy
msgid "(<i>Yawn</i>)"
msgstr "(<i>Bâillement</i>)"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:222
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Ugh, what a headache. I shouldn’t have drunk so much... now nature calls."
msgstr ""
"Pfiou, quelle gueule de bois. Je n’aurais pas dû boire autant... et voilà, "
"la nature m'appelle."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#. Delfador's woken up in the middle of the night to go use the latrines
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:238
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Disgusting. Alduin really needs to invent a spell for cleaning latrines.\n"
"\n"
"Mayhaps as High Advisor I can finally get someone to research that... "
"(<i>yawn</i>)"
msgstr ""
"C'est répugnant. Alduin devrait vraiment envisager d'inventer un sort pour "
"l'entretien des latrines.\n"
"Peut-être qu'en tant que Haut Conseiller, je pourrais enfin lancer des "
"recherches dans ce domaine... (<i>bâillement</i>)"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:260
#, fuzzy
msgid "Oh!"
msgstr "Oh!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:264
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You have startled me, Your Majesty. The darkest hour of night is hardly a "
"queenly time to be about — should you not be asleep with Garard? ’tis not "
"every day that Wesnoth wins a war."
msgstr ""
"Votre Majesté, vous m'avez surpris. L'heure la plus noire de la nuit n'est "
"guère propice pour qu'une reine se promène ainsi — ne devriez-vous pas "
"reposer à côté de Garard ? Ce n'est pas tous les jours que Wesnoth remporte "
"une guerre."

#. [message]: speaker=Asheviere
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:269
#, fuzzy
msgid "Hello Delfador — or should I say, “Delfador the Great.”"
msgstr "Bonjour Delfador — ou devrais-je plutôt dire, « Delfador le Grand. »"

#. [message]: speaker=Asheviere
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:273
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Such pleasure to once more speak with my husband’s famous right hand. I "
"never did properly thank you for returning me back to him, all those years "
"ago."
msgstr ""
"Quel plaisir de m'entretenir à nouveau avec le fameux bras droit de mon "
"époux. Je ne vous ai jamais véritablement remercié de m'avoir ramenée à lui, "
"il y a tant d'années."

#. [message]: speaker=Asheviere
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:281
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You’re a powerful man, a <i>dangerous</i> man, Delfador. I pity the fool who "
"finds themselves on the wrong end of your staff... yet I oft pity even more "
"so the fool who rules behind it, so consumed by the minutiae of war."
msgstr ""
"Vous êtes un homme puissant, un homme <i>dangereux</i>, Delfador. Je plains "
"le malheureux qui se retrouve du mauvais côté de votre bâton… mais je plains "
"encore davantage celui qui se cache derrière, si absorbé par les menus "
"détails de la guerre."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:286
#, fuzzy
msgid "Err... I’m not sure I follow, Your Highness—"
msgstr "Euh... Je ne suis pas certain de vous suivre, Votre Majesté…"

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:299
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"What’s going on here? Careful, Delfador — don’t believe a word she says."
msgstr ""
"Que se passe-t-il ici ? Prends garde, Delfador — ne crois pas un mot de ce "
"qu'elle dit."

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:303
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Woman, are you not satisfied with my son; you must have my wizard too!? Away "
"with you, wench, and save your lacquered tongue for another day!"
msgstr ""
"Femme, n'as-tu pas assez de mon fils ? Te faut-il également mon magicien ? "
"Va-t-en, sorcière, et garde ta langue mielleuse pour une autre fois !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:307
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Peace, peace! Wesnoth stands triumphant; there’s no need for quarreling!"
msgstr ""
"Du calme, du calme ! Wesnoth triomphe ; il n'y a aucune raison de se "
"quereller !"

#. [message]: speaker=Asheviere
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:311
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"It’s quite all right, Delfador; I take no offense at my husband’s cruel "
"words. Far be it from me to interfere in military matters — the king and his "
"new advisor have doubtless much to speak on. I graciously take my leave."
msgstr ""
"Tout va bien, Delfador ; je ne prends pas mal les mots cruels de mon mari. "
"Je ne vais pas m’immiscer dans les affaires militaires — le roi et son "
"nouveau conseiller doivent avoir bien des sujets de discussion. Je vais "
"prendre congé avec grâce."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:324
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"That seemed a little extreme, m’lord! Surely a little politeness would not "
"go amiss, especially with regards to your own blood! I’ve heard nothing but "
"praise for the queen from most of the court."
msgstr ""
"Cela m'a semblé un peu excessif, sire ! Une touche de politesse n’aurait "
"certainement pas fait de mal, surtout que cela concerne votre propre "
"famille ! Je n’ai entendu que des louanges au sujet de la reine par la "
"plupart des membres de la cour."

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:328
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"They don’t know her. You don’t know her. All is not well with my family, "
"Delfador."
msgstr ""
"Ils ne la connaissent pas. Vous ne la connaissez pas. Tout ne tourne pas "
"rond au sein de ma famille, Delfador."

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:337
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"My ancestors — the first king and the first queen — led the entire race of "
"men across the ocean to found Wesnoth. Those two understood each other. They "
"saved us all from the terrors of the west. They raised a strong prince, a "
"good son."
msgstr ""
"Mes ancêtres — le premier roi et la première reine — ont conduit toute la "
"race humaine à travers l'océan pour fonder Wesnoth. Ces deux-là se "
"comprenaient. Ils nous ont sauvés de toutes les horreurs de l'ouest. Ils ont "
"élevé un prince solide, un bon fils."

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:341
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"And what of I? This ruinous war, just to satisfy my own ambition? All was "
"nearly lost. Without your magic, all might have been. I’ve made so many "
"mistakes, my friend."
msgstr ""
"Et qu'en est-il de moi ? Cette guerre dévastatrice, simplement pour "
"satisfaire mes propres ambitions ? On a failli tout perdre. Sans votre "
"magie, tout aurait pu l'être. J'ai commis tant d'erreurs, mon ami."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:349
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"No man is without flaws, Your Highness. Certainly not you and I. But I’ve "
"followed you through thick and thin, and together we have always emerged "
"triumphant."
msgstr ""
"Personne n’est sans défaut, Votre Altesse. Pas vous ni moi, en tout cas. "
"Mais je vous ai toujours suivi, dans les bons comme dans les mauvais "
"moments, et ensemble, nous avons toujours surmonté l'adversité."

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:378
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:347
#, fuzzy
msgid "Father."
msgstr "Père"

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:383
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Boy? This is a pleasant surprise; I thought you were with your uncle, "
"guarding Fort Garard. Come to celebrate the war’s end with us, did you? It "
"is good to see you again."
msgstr ""
"Fiston ? Quelle agréable surprise ! Je croyais que tu étais avec ton oncle, "
"à garder le Fort Garard. Es-tu venu célébrer la fin de la guerre avec nous ? "
"C'est un plaisir de te revoir."

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:389
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Hold on, what’s the matter with— you’re <b><i>injured</i></b>!? What "
"happened! Where’s that useless Methor when you need him?!"
msgstr ""
"Attends, quoi ? T’es <b><i>blessé</i></b> !? Qu’est-ce qui s’est passé ? Où "
"est ce bon à rien de Methor, jamais là quand on a besoin de lui !?"

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:397
#, fuzzy
msgid "It’s about your—"
msgstr "C’est à propos de votre..."

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:405
#, fuzzy
msgid "...Father, it’s Uncle. Prince Arand."
msgstr "... Père, il s'agit de mon oncle. Le Prince Arand."

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#. Eldred doesn’t show a lot of emotion here. He's lying, and not very good at it
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:411
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"He’s found the Sceptre of Fire. He declared his claim to the throne, and "
"seized control of Fort Garard. My bodyguards and I tried to stop him, but we "
"didn’t even get close. I barely made it out alive."
msgstr ""
"Il a trouvé le Sceptre du Feu. Il a revendiqué son droit au trône et s'est "
"emparé du Fort Garard. Mes gardes du corps et moi avons tenté de l'arrêter, "
"mais nous n'avons même pas pu nous en approcher. J'ai à peine réussi à m'en "
"sortir vivant."

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:415
#, fuzzy
msgid "Arand tried to kill me, Father. He’s coming for you next."
msgstr "Arand a tenté de me tuer, Père. Il en aura après toi ensuite."

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:421
#, fuzzy
msgid "Garard—?"
msgstr "Garard—?"

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:425
#, fuzzy
msgid "WHAT!?"
msgstr "QUOI!?"

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:435
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"That TREASONOUS son-of-a, son-of— I knew something felt suspicious lately."
msgstr ""
"Ce fils de traître, ce fils de... Je me doutais qu’il y avait quelque chose "
"de bizarre ces derniers temps."

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:439
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"It all makes sense now. Arand is my spymaster — of course the spies told me "
"nothing. And Arand warned me that others were searching for the Sceptre... "
"to trick me into sending away Lionel, my most loyal general!"
msgstr ""
"Tout s'explique maintenant. Arand est mon maître espion —bien sûr, les "
"espions ne m’ont rien dit. Et Arand m’a averti que d’autres cherchaient le "
"Sceptre... pour me manipuler et m'inciter à envoyer Lionel, mon général le "
"plus loyal, loin de moi !"

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:444
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"How DARE he threaten me? How dare he lay a FINGER on my son? I’ll see him "
"hang for this."
msgstr ""
"Comment ose-t-il me menacer ? Comment ose-t-il lever la MAIN sur mon fils ? "
"Je le ferai pendre pour cela."

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:448
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Delfador, take command of the cavalry; my personal royal cavalry — they’re "
"the only ones I still trust. Ride to Fort Garard and burn it to the ground!"
msgstr ""
"Delfador, prends le commandement de la cavalerie ; ma cavalerie royale "
"personnelle — ce sont les seuls en qui j’ai encore confiance. Montez à Fort "
"Garard et réduisez-le en cendres !"

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:452
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I want every one of those traitors dead! Return with Arand’s head— his HEAD! "
"Or don’t return at all. Do you understand!?"
msgstr ""
"Je veux voir tous ces traîtres morts ! Ramenez-moi la tête d'Arand — sa "
"TÊTE ! sa TÊTE ! Ou ne revenez pas du tout. Est-ce clair !?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:456
#, fuzzy
msgid "Yes, Your Majesty!"
msgstr "Oui, Sire !"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:472
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Delfador, I couldn’t help but overhear. Prince Arand, the king’s brother?? "
"That can’t be."
msgstr ""
"Delfador, je n’ai pas pu m’empêcher d’écouter. Le prince Arand, le frère du "
"roi ? Ça ne peut pas être vrai."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:476
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The young Prince Eldred’s wounds are clear as day, Deoran. Will you ride "
"with us? Every moment we delay is another chance for Arand to rally more "
"rebels to his cause."
msgstr ""
"Les blessures du jeune Prince Eldred sont bien visibles, Deoran. Tu viens "
"avec nous ? Chaque instant que nous perdons permet à Arand de rallier plus "
"de rebelles à sa cause."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:480
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"But a sentence of death, without even trial? Arand is thoughtful and quiet, "
"and not known to be ambitious."
msgstr ""
"Mais une condamnation à mort, sans même un procès ? Arand est un homme "
"réfléchi et réservé, et il n'est pas connu pour nourrir des ambitions "
"démesurées."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#. this mirrors Methor's request to Lionel in S10x
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:485
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The king has commanded his death, yes. But you are the one sent to carry it "
"out. You don’t... <b><i>have</i></b> to go, you know. At least not so "
"hastily."
msgstr ""
"Le roi a ordonné sa mort, oui. Mais c'est vous qui êtes chargé de "
"l'exécuter. Vous n'êtes pas obligé de partir sur-le-champ, vous savez. Du "
"moins, pas aussi précipitamment."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:489
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Refuse Garard’s order. Hold back, dispatch scouts, and gather more "
"information before committing so much of the army to this attack. Wesnoth "
"can scant afford a civil war, and certainly not so soon after the orcs!"
msgstr ""
"Refuse l’ordre de Garard. Prends du recul, envoie des éclaireurs, et récolte "
"plus d’informations avant d’engager autant de troupes dans cette attaque. "
"Wesnoth ne peut pas se permettre une guerre civile, surtout pas juste après "
"celle des orcs !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:493
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Are you mad?! It’s neither your place nor mine to second-guess His Majesty. "
"Especially not now, when he needs loyalty more than ever."
msgstr ""
"Es-tu fou ? Ce n’est ni ton rôle ni le mien de douter de Sa Majesté. Pas "
"maintenant, surtout pas quand il a plus que jamais besoin de loyauté."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:497
#, fuzzy
msgid "Delfador, I really worry—"
msgstr "Delfador, je suis vraiment inquiet..."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:501
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"And... besides, I’ve lived half my life fighting alongside the king, "
"fighting to gain his favor. Today I’m “The Great”, but I didn’t even have a "
"name before I first began to battle."
msgstr ""
"Et... de surcroît, j’ai consacré la moitié de ma vie à lutter aux côtés du "
"roi, à me battre pour mériter sa faveur. Aujourd'hui, je suis « Delfador le "
"Grand », alors que je n'avais même pas de nom avant de prendre les armes "
"pour la première fois."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:505
#, fuzzy
msgid "Without that, who am I? I don’t want to end up exiled, like you were..."
msgstr ""
"Sans cela, qui suis-je ? Je ne voudrais pas finir exilé, comme tu l'as été..."

#. [unit]: type=Knight
#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:517
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:395
#, fuzzy
msgid "Sir Kaylan"
msgstr "Sieur Kaylan"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/11x_Revelry.cfg:536
#, fuzzy
msgid "Royal cavalry, form up on me! We go at once!"
msgstr ""
"Cavalerie royale, regroupez-vous derrière moi ! Nous partons immédiatement !"

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:11
msgid "The Traitor"
msgstr "Le traître"

#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:29
#, fuzzy
msgid "Royal Cavalry"
msgstr "Cavalerie Royale"

#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:56
#, fuzzy
msgid "Luraery"
msgstr "Luraery"

#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:71
msgid "Aelyn"
msgstr "Aelyn"

#. [message]: speaker=Arand
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:272
#, fuzzy
msgid "Fall back! Hold the walls, protect the fort!"
msgstr "Repliez-vous ! Tenez les murs, protégez le fort !"

#. [message]: speaker=Arand
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:352
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The scouts bring grim news — a fearsome army rides against us! Long have I "
"dreaded this moment. Rally together, fight as one, and we will assuredly "
"triumph in the coming civil war!"
msgstr ""
"Les éclaireurs apportent de sinistres nouvelles — une armée redoutable se "
"dirige contre nous ! Cela fait longtemps que je redoute ce moment. "
"Rassemblez-vous, combattez unis, et nous sortirons victorieux de cette "
"guerre civile !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:378
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Curses, we have already been spotted. Time is of the essence; we must strike "
"before Arand can turn more Wesnothians to his cause!"
msgstr ""
"Malédiction, nous avons déjà été repérés. Le temps presse ; nous devons "
"frapper avant qu'Arand ne rallie davantage de Wesnothiens à sa cause !"

#. [message]: speaker=Kaylan
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:413
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The king’s personal cavalry stands at your command, great Delfador! Direct "
"us as you will, and the traitor prince shall fall beneath our hooves!"
msgstr ""
"La cavalerie personnelle du roi est à vos ordres, grand Delfador ! Donnez-"
"nous vos instructions, et le prince félon sera terrassé sous nos sabots !"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:421
#, fuzzy
msgid "Defeat Prince Arand"
msgstr "Vaincre le Prince Arand"

#. [object]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:443
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Your veteran soldiers have been left behind with Deoran <b>(you’ll see them "
"again next scenario)</b>, but you can instead recruit Cavalrymen and "
"Horsemen!\n"
"\n"
"Cavalrymen are general-purpose mounted infantry, with moderate damage for a "
"moderate price. Horsemen are more expensive, but their risky charge attack "
"deals heavy damage."
msgstr ""
"Vos soldats vétérans sont restés derrière avec Deoran <b>(vous les "
"retrouverez dans le prochain scénario)</b>, mais vous pouvez recruter des "
"cavaliers et des hussards à la place !\n"
"\n"
"Les hussards sont des troupes montées polyvalentes, avec des dégâts modérés "
"pour un prix raisonnable. Les Cavaliers sont plus chers, mais leur charge "
"peut infliger de lourds dégâts."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:449
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Garard’s Royal Cavalry are loyal and skilled, but neither Horsemen nor "
"Cavalrymen are well-suited for fighting Arand’s army of Spearmen and "
"Pikemen. My magic shall have to make up the difference."
msgstr ""
"La Cavalerie Royale de Garard est loyale et compétente, mais ni les hussards "
"ni les Cavaliers ne sont vraiment adaptés pour affronter l’armée d'Arand "
"composée de Lanciers et de Hallebardiers. Ma magie devra faire la différence."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:453
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If only my outlaws and veterans could have marched fast enough to keep up. "
"If the king’s own brother is an usurper, who in Wesnoth can I really trust?"
msgstr ""
"Si seulement mes hors-la-loi et mes vétérans avaient marché assez vite pour "
"nous suivre. Si le propre frère du roi est un usurpateur, à qui puis-je "
"vraiment faire confiance à Wesnoth?"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. said by a male cavalryman or horseman
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:467
#, fuzzy
msgid "Fight on without me, friends! Fight for our king!"
msgstr ""
"Continuez à vous battre sans moi, mes amis ! Battez-vous pour notre roi !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:479
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"There’s right where I’d stood, back when I fought my first real battle. How "
"simple everything seemed back then..."
msgstr ""
"C’est exactement là que je me tenais, au moment de mon premier vrai combat. "
"Comme tout paraissait simple à l’époque…"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:491
#, fuzzy
msgid "Welcome to Garard’s Wold, last civilized town north of the Great River."
msgstr ""
"Bienvenue aux collines de Garard, dernière ville civilisée au nord du Grand "
"Fleuve"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:513
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Such devastation. Garard ordered us to “burn it to the ground”, and we did..."
msgstr ""
"Quelle destruction. Garard nous avait dit de 'tout réduire en cendres', et "
"c'est ce que nous avons fait..."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:547
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The rebellion is broken! In the name of King Garard and the royal scepter, I "
"strike you down!"
msgstr ""
"La rébellion est anéantie ! Je te frappe au nom du roi Garard et du sceptre "
"royal!"

#. [message]: speaker=Arand
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:552
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"King Garard?! My brother sent you? But I thought—? Wait, stop, please, I "
"don’t understand!"
msgstr ""
"Le roi Garard ?! Mon frère t’a envoyé ? Mais je croyais… ? Attends, arrête, "
"s’il te plaît, je ne comprends pas !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:565
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The young Prince Eldred told us how you tried to claim the throne for "
"yourself, Arand. You are mortally wounded — confess now, and King Garard may "
"forgive you in death."
msgstr ""
"Le jeune prince Eldred nous a raconté comment tu as tenté de t'emparer du "
"trône, Arand. Tu es gravement blessé — avoue maintenant, et le roi Garard "
"pourra peut-être te pardonner aprés ta mort."

#. [message]: speaker=Arand
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:569
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"By the Sceptre, I swear I have never conspired against my brother Garard. "
"Eldred is the traitor! Eldred and Asheviere are the traitors, not me!"
msgstr ""
"Sur le Sceptre, je jure que je n'ai jamais comploté contre mon frère Garard. "
"C'est Eldred le traître ! Eldred et Asheviere sont les traîtres, pas moi !"

#. [message]: speaker=Arand
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:578
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"My life runs short; you must believe my tale. For some time now my spies "
"have heard whispers of a terrible conspiracy, a plot to overthrow the very "
"king himself.\n"
"\n"
"’Twas not a fortnight hence that my suspicions were confirmed — I gained "
"incontrovertible evidence proving the chief conspirators to be none other "
"than the queen and the prince, two of my brother’s closest companions!"
msgstr ""
"Ma fin approche ; vous devez croire mon histoire. Depuis un certain temps, "
"mes espions ont rapporté des rumeurs d'une conspiration terrible, un plan "
"pour renverser le roi en personne.\n"
"\n"
"Il n'y a pas plus de deux semaines, mes doutes ont été confirmés — j'ai "
"acquis des preuves irréfutables prouvant que les principaux conspirateurs "
"sont la reine et le prince, deux des plus intimes compagnons de mon frère !"

#. [message]: speaker=Arand
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:584
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Yet no sooner did this news arrive than my bodyguards and I were set upon by "
"Eldred himself, so bold as to strike even during the day!\n"
"\n"
"I slew several of his fighters and grievously wounded the young prince, yet "
"barely escaped to Fort Garard before my guards were overwhelmed."
msgstr ""
"À peine cette nouvelle m’était parvenue, que mes gardes du corps et moi "
"fûmes attaqués par Eldred en personne, assez audacieux pour nous frapper en "
"plein jour !\n"
"\n"
"J'abattis plusieurs de ses guerriers et blessai grièvement le jeune prince, "
"pourtant je parvenais à m'enfuir de justesse vers Fort Garard avant que mes "
"gardes ne fussent submergés."

#. [message]: speaker=Arand
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:590
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"And now it seems that Eldred has found a way to finish me off after all..."
msgstr ""
"Et maintenant, il semble qu'Eldred ait trouvé un moyen de me réduire au "
"silence..."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:595
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I sense the ring of truth in your words... But if what you say is true, why "
"fight when we approached instead of surrender? To my eyes, your resistance "
"only sealed your guilt."
msgstr ""
"Je perçois de la vérité dans tes paroles... Mais si ce que tu dis est vrai, "
"pourquoi as-tu lutté quand nous nous sommes approchés au lieu de te rendre ? "
"À mes yeux, ta résistance n'a fait que sceller ta culpabilité."

#. [message]: speaker=Arand
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:600
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Can you blame me? Rolling waves of mud smashing my fortress to bits — I "
"thought this some foul magic of the queen’s, here to finish what Eldred "
"failed to do! For many months now have I suspected the influence of a "
"necromancer most powerful..."
msgstr ""
"Puis-je en être blâmé ? Des vagues de boue déferlaient sur ma forteresse, la "
"réduisant en miettes. Je crus à un mauvais sortilège de la reine, venue "
"achever ce qu'Eldred n'avait pu faire ! Depuis des mois, je soupçonnais "
"l'influence d'un nécromancien des plus puissants…"

#. [message]: speaker=Arand
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:607
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Can you blame me? Rolling waves of fire burning my fortress to cinders — I "
"thought this some foul magic of the queen’s, here to finish what Eldred "
"failed to do! For many months now have I suspected the influence of a "
"necromancer most powerful..."
msgstr ""
"Puis-je en être blâmé ? Des vagues de feu déferlaient, réduisant ma "
"forteresse en cendres. Je pensais qu'il s'agissait d'un sortilège maléfique "
"de la reine, venue achever ce qu'Eldred n'avait pu faire ! Depuis des mois, "
"je soupçonnais l'influence d'un nécromancien des plus puissants..."

#. [message]: speaker=Arand
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:614
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Can you blame me? I thought your cavalry and magic to be more of the same — "
"servants of the queen, here to finish what Eldred failed to do! For many "
"months now have I suspected the influence of a necromancer most powerful..."
msgstr ""
"Puis-je en être blâmé ? Je croyais ta cavalerie et ta magie être n'était "
"comme le reste — que des serviteurs de la reine, venus achever ce qu’Eldred "
"n’avait pas réussi à faire ! Depuis plusieurs mois, je soupçonne l'influence "
"d’un nécromancien des plus puissants…"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:620
#, fuzzy
msgid "Malal. He is dead now."
msgstr "Malal. Il est mort maintenant."

#. [message]: speaker=Arand
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:624
#, fuzzy
msgid "But if you are here with me, then Eldred is alone with the king?"
msgstr "Mais si vous êtes ici avec moi, alors Eldred est seul avec le roi ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Arand
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:639
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"So much blood... please, you must believe me! Save my brother... save "
"Wesnoth..."
msgstr "Que de sang… croyez-moi ! Sauvez mon frère… sauvez Wesnoth…"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:682
#, fuzzy
msgid "Prince Eldred? What are you doing here?"
msgstr "Prince Eldred ? Que faites-vous ici ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:692
#, fuzzy
msgid "There he is! Get him!"
msgstr "Le voilà ! Attrapez-le !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/12_The_Traitor.cfg:700
#, fuzzy
msgid "Huh? Wha—"
msgstr "Hein ? Quoi ?"

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:23
#, fuzzy
msgid "Revelry, Revisited"
msgstr "Les festivités, revisitées"

#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:41
#, fuzzy
msgid "Deoran’s Company"
msgstr "La compagnie de Deoran"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:73
#, fuzzy
msgid "Sir Grey"
msgstr "Sieur Grey"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:100
#, fuzzy
msgid "Sir Johan"
msgstr "Sieur Johan"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:107
#, fuzzy
msgid "Sir Gwido"
msgstr "Sieur Gwido"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:171
#, fuzzy
msgid "I’ve pillaged $gold_pickup gold from Eldred’s treasury!"
msgstr "J'ai pillé $gold_pickup pièces d'or dans le trésor d'Eldred !"

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:290
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:294
#, fuzzy
msgid "So."
msgstr "Alors."

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:302
#, fuzzy
msgid "Guess you’re the boss now."
msgstr "Je suppose que c'est vous le patron maintenant."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:306
#, fuzzy
msgid "It would seem as such. Would that Delfador had stayed."
msgstr "Il semblerait bien. Si seulement Delfador était resté."

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:312
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"...hey, is it true that you’ve lived with elves? I hear they’re the greatest "
"bestest most beautifulest creatures there are!"
msgstr ""
"…Dis, c’est vrai que tu as vécu avec des elfes ? J’ai entendu dire que ce "
"sont les créatures les plus merveilleuses, les plus belles et les plus "
"extraordinaires qui soient !"

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:313
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"female^...hey, is it true that you’ve lived with elves? I hear they’re the "
"greatest bestest most beautifulest creatures there are!"
msgstr ""
"…Dis, c’est vrai que tu as vécu avec des elfes ? J’ai entendu dire que ce "
"sont les créatures les plus merveilleuses, les plus belles et les plus "
"extraordinaires qui soient !"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#. referencing the events of TSG
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:318
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Elves? No. Be not fooled by a pretty face — I have seen even the noblest "
"elven sage corrupted to such darkness as to rival the foulest human or orc."
msgstr ""
"Les elfes ? Non. Ne vous laissez pas abuser par un joli minois — j'ai vu "
"même le plus noble des sages elfes corrompu à un tel degré de noirceur que "
"cela rivaliserait avec celui du plus vil des humains ou des orcs."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:322
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Although, I suppose there is at least one young elf of my acquaintance to "
"whom I might ascribe such virtues. My thoughts find her often, in these dark "
"times."
msgstr ""
"Je suppose toutefois qu'il existe au moins une jeune elfe parmi mes "
"connaissances à qui je pourrais attribuer de telles vertus. Je pense souvent "
"à elle, en ces temps sombres."

#. [message]: speaker=Kestrel
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:341
#, fuzzy
msgid "Sir, Delfador and the Royal Cavalry are out of sight."
msgstr "Monsieur, Delfador et la cavalerie royale sont hors de vue."

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:351
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"All healed up? Excellent. Come out of the rain and join me in my tent. We’ll "
"soon put this rebellion to rest."
msgstr ""
"Tu es complètement rétabli ? Parfait. Viens te mettre à l'abri de la pluie "
"en me rejoignant dans ma tente. Nous allons bientôt mettre fin à cette "
"rébellion."

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:357
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I admit, I was worried about you, son. <i>“Soft”</i> I thought — if I should "
"fall, could you truly lead our people to victory? I wanted to toughen you up."
msgstr ""
"Je dois admettre que je m’inquiétais pour toi, mon fils. Je pensais que tu "
"étais « trop doux » — si je venais à tomber, serais-tu réellement capable de "
"mener notre peuple à la victoire ? Je voulais t’endurcir."

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#. I think this is the only time Garard actually calls Eldred by his name. Not "boy" or "son"
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:362
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"But now? Sniffing out treachery in our own family? Taking it upon yourself "
"to bring Arand to justice! You may have failed to defeat him, but failure "
"does not diminish the trying. You did well today, Eldred."
msgstr ""
"Mais maintenant ? Repérer la trahison au sein de notre propre famille ? "
"Prendre l'initiative de traduire Arand en justice ! Tu n'as pas réussi à le "
"vaincre certes, mais cet échec ne retire rien à l'effort fourni. Tu t‘es "
"bien comporté aujourd'hui, Eldred."

#. [message]: speaker=Garard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:388
#, fuzzy
msgid "(shocked) You—"
msgstr "(choqué) Toi—"

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:408
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:998
#, fuzzy
msgid "Finally."
msgstr "Enfin."

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:418
#, fuzzy
msgid "Wake! Alarm—"
msgstr "Alerte ! Réveillez-vous !"

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:422
#, fuzzy
msgid "(gulp, deep breath)"
msgstr "(déglutit, inspire profondément)"

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:434
#, fuzzy
msgid "WAKE! ALARM! DEORAN HAS SLAIN THE KING!"
msgstr "RÉVEILLEZ-VOUS ! ALERTE ! DEORAN A TUÉ LE ROI !"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:439
#, fuzzy
msgid "What!?"
msgstr "Quoi!?"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:445
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Garard truly is dead, and by the sword at that! Eldred was the last to "
"enter..."
msgstr ""
"Garard est bel et bien mort, et par l'épée ! Eldred a été le dernier à "
"entrer..."

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:449
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"See Deoran there, standing now at the mouth of my father’s tent? He strikes "
"in cold blood, at the height of my father’s triumph! He takes revenge for "
"his long years of exile! Only a heart shaped by hate and twisted by elves "
"could commit such a foul deed!"
msgstr ""
"Regardez Deoran, là, debout devant l'entrée de la tente de mon père ? Il a "
"frappé de sang-froid, alors même que mon père était au sommet de son "
"triomphe ! Il se venge de ses années d'exil ! Un cœur façonné par la haine "
"et corrompu par les elfes est le seul capable d'un acte aussi odieux !"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:453
#, fuzzy
msgid "No! Eldred is—"
msgstr "Non ! C'est Eldred…"

#. [message]: speaker=eldred4
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:457
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Calamity! The ambassador always seemed so polite! How could he do this? How "
"could we let him do this?!"
msgstr ""
"Catastrophe ! L'ambassadeur, lui qui paraissait toujours si poli ! Comment a-"
"t-il pu faire ça ? Comment avons-nous pu le laisser faire ?!"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:461
#, fuzzy
msgid "No! I—"
msgstr "Non! Je—"

#. [message]: speaker=eldred3
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:465
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"We all know that Deoran was not loved by the king. All this while he must "
"have been biding his time, plotting his attack! And look, that outlaw of "
"Delfador’s stands beside him, witness and accomplice to the crime!"
msgstr ""
"Nous savons tous que Deoran n’était pas apprécié du roi. Pendant tout ce "
"temps, il a dû attendre son heure, complotant son attaque ! Et regarde, le "
"hors-la-loi de Delfador se tient à ses côtés, témoin et complice du crime !"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:470
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"No, no! $companion_name is not my accomplice— I mean, neither of us are "
"accomplices— that is to say—"
msgstr ""
"Non, non ! $companion_name n'est pas mon complice — enfin, aucun de nous "
"deux n'est complice — c'est-à-dire…"

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:479
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Ignore the killer’s murderous ramblings. Rally, soldiers of Wesnoth! Slay "
"Deoran and avenge the king!"
msgstr ""
"Ignorez les propos haineux de ce tueur. Soldats de Wesnoth, unissez-vous ! "
"Tuez Deoran et vengez notre roi !"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:512
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"(aghast) Horrors below, Garard’s own son; what has happened to my beautiful "
"kingdom? How—"
msgstr ""
"(abasourdi) Horreurs à nos pieds, le propre fils de Garard… Qu’est-il arrivé "
"à notre beau royaume ? Comment…"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:516
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I don’t— what do I do? They all believe Eldred!? I’m not ready for a fight!"
msgstr ""
"Je ne… que dois-je faire ? Ils croient tous Eldred ?! Je ne suis pas prêt "
"pour un combat !"

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:521
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Listen boss, I’m not much for politics, but I know when to run and that’s "
"now! We’ve got to get out of here!"
msgstr ""
"Écoute, patron, la politique, c'est pas mon truc, mais je sais quand il faut "
"se barrer, et c'est maintenant ! On doit se tirer d'ici !"

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:522
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"female^Listen boss, I’m not much for politics, but I know when to run and "
"that’s now! We’ve got to get out of here!"
msgstr ""
"Écoute, patron, la politique, c'est pas mon truc, mais je sais quand il faut "
"se barrer, et c'est maintenant ! On doit se tirer d'ici !"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:526
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I— yes, you’re right! With Garard dead, Delfador commands the greatest "
"honest force left in Wesnoth, and he has no idea what has just transpired! "
"Delfador must be warned."
msgstr ""
"Je… oui, tu as raison ! Avec Garard mort, Delfador commande la plus grande "
"force loyale qu'il reste à Wesnoth, et il n’a aucune idée de ce qui vient de "
"se passer ! Delfador doit être prévenu."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:530
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"If we are lucky, we may yet be able to save Arand from Delfador’s ill-"
"informed assault. But even barring that, Delfador’s leadership can surely "
"rally enough soldiers to oppose Eldred by force of arms!\n"
"\n"
"$companion_name, go, now! Slip away along the eastern road!"
msgstr ""
"Si la chance nous sourit, nous pourrons peut-être encore sauver Arand de "
"l'assaut de Delfador qui a été mal informé. Mais même sans cela, le "
"commandement de Delfador devrait pouvoir réunir assez de soldats pour faire "
"face à Eldred par la force !\n"
"$companion_name, vas-y, maintenant ! Prends la route de l'est en toute "
"discrétion !"

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:541
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"...hey, how come you’re not following? Don’t even think about sacrificing "
"yourself because of “chivalry” or some other bunk."
msgstr ""
"Hé, pourquoi tu ne me suis pas ? Tu ne songes tout de même pas à te "
"sacrifier à cause de la « chevalerie » ou de n’importe quelle autre autre "
"connerie de ce genre."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:545
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Nothing so heroic. Wesnoth’s forces may believe me a conspirator now, but I "
"will not give up on them so easily. If I fight my way into a private "
"audience with each leader I’m sure I can make them see the truth about "
"Eldred — Garard’s poor family relationships were no secret.\n"
"\n"
"Even if I can but convince commanders to delay their support for the traitor "
"prince, that will give Delfador and me much-needed time to gather gold "
"before our next battle!"
msgstr ""
"Rien d'aussi héroïque. Les forces de Wesnoth me prennent peut-être pour un "
"conspirateur à présent, mais je ne les laisserai pas tomber aussi "
"facilement. Si je réussis à me frayer un chemin jusqu'à chaque commandant en "
"privé, je suis sûr de pouvoir leur faire comprendre la vérité sur Eldred — "
"les relations familiales de Garard étaient loin d’être secrètes.\n"
"\n"
"Même si je ne parviens qu'à convaincre quelques commandants de reporter leur "
"soutien au prince félon, cela nous donnera, à Delfador et à moi, tout le "
"temps nécessaire pour rassembler de l’or avant notre prochaine bataille !"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:551
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"<i>Defeating enemy leaders will increase your starting gold in the next "
"scenario.</i>"
msgstr ""
"<i>Vaincre les chefs ennemis augmentera votre or de départ dans le prochain "
"scénario.</i>"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:555
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"When at last my strength is spent, I will flee through the forest — my steed "
"is elf-stock, and no rival bred in Wesnoth can outpace its haste amongst the "
"trees. But the more support I can garner now, the better our position will "
"be in the future!"
msgstr ""
"Quand la force me fera défaut, je fuirai à travers la forêt — mon destrier "
"est d'origine elfique, aucun cheval de Wesnoth ne pourra rivaliser avec sa "
"vitesse dans les bois. Mais plus je parviendrai à obtenir de soutien "
"maintenant, meilleure sera notre position à l'avenir !"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:559
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Now make haste, and godspeed! You must reunite with Delfador; I will send "
"what soldiers I can spare after you!"
msgstr ""
"Maintenant dépêche-toi, et que Dieu te garde ! Tu dois rejoindre Delfador ; "
"je t’enverrai les soldats que je peux te prêter !"

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:567
#, fuzzy
msgid "Avenge the king! Don’t let them escape!"
msgstr "Vengez le roi ! Ne les laissez pas s'échapper !"

#. [event]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:614
#, fuzzy
msgid "$gold_pickup gold"
msgstr "$gold_pickup pièces d'or"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:629
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Defeat as many enemy leaders as possible before Deoran is defeated\n"
"    <i>(each defeated leader yields bonus gold in the next scenario)</i>"
msgstr ""
"Vaincre un maximum de chefs ennemis avant la défaite de Deoran.\n"
"    <i>(Chaque chef vaincu rapporte de l'or bonus dans le scénario "
"suivant.)</i>"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#. $|escape_turns_remaining is probably between 0 and 10
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:636
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Evacuate veteran units along the eastern road ($|escape_turns_remaining "
"turns remaining)"
msgstr ""
"Évacuer les unités expérimentées le long de la route est ($|"
"escape_turns_remaining tours restants)"

#. [note]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:643
#, fuzzy
msgid "When an enemy leader is defeated, their remaining soldiers will flee."
msgstr ""
"Lorsqu'un chef ennemi est vaincu, les soldats restants prennent la fuite."

#. [note]: description=<b>
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:647
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1089
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1240
#, fuzzy
msgid "This is the second-to-last scenario."
msgstr "C'est l'avant-dernier scénario."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:673
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Units that escape to the east will be available to recall in the next "
"scenario, but units that do not escape will be lost (either scattered or "
"killed) — including units on your recall list! The eastern path will remain "
"open until the end of turn {ESCAPE_TURNS}.\n"
"\n"
"You should evacuate enough veterans to have a strong recall list next "
"scenario, but also defeat enough enemy leaders so that you’ll have gold for "
"recalling."
msgstr ""
"Les unités qui s'échappent vers l'est pourront être rappelées lors du "
"prochain scénario, mais celles qui ne s'échappent pas seront perdues "
"(dispersées ou détruites), y compris celles figurant sur votre liste de "
"rappel ! La voie orientale restera ouverte jusqu'à la fin du tour "
"{ESCAPE_TURNS}.\n"
"\n"
"Vous devriez évacuer suffisamment de vétérans pour constituer une liste de "
"rappel solide pour le prochain scénario, mais aussi vaincre suffisamment de "
"chefs ennemis pour disposer de suffisamment d'or pour les rappels."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:702
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Fleeing too quickly will only seal my guilt in the eyes of Wesnoth’s "
"commanders. I do not intend to run until I have no other choice!"
msgstr ""
"Fuir trop vite ne ferait que confirmer ma culpabilité aux yeux des "
"commandants de Wesnoth. Je n'ai pas l'intention de m'enfuir tant que je "
"n'aurai pas d'autre choix !"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:716
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I hear orc-drums approaching the eastern road! Any more who wish to flee — "
"now is your last chance."
msgstr ""
"J'entends les tambours des orcs approcher de la route est ! Ceux qui "
"souhaitent encore fuir — c'est votre dernière occasion."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:721
#, fuzzy
msgid "I hear orc-drums approaching the eastern road! Our time runs short."
msgstr ""
"J'entends des tambours d'orcs qui approchent de la route à l'est ! Le temps "
"nous est compté."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:753
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1103
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You will now start the next scenario with $bonus_gold total gold (plus "
"$s11_carryover carryover from Delfador)"
msgstr ""
"Vous allez maintenant commencer le scénario suivant avec un total d'or de "
"$bonus_gold (plus $s11_carryover reporté de Delfador)."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:758
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1108
#, fuzzy
msgid "You will now start the next scenario with $bonus_gold total gold!"
msgstr ""
"Vous allez maintenant commencer le scénario suivant avec $bonus_gold pièces "
"d'or!"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:774
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"One leader is defeated. I had hoped to gain a new ally, but depriving Eldred "
"and buying time is good enough. And now that this keep is ours, I can "
"recruit more soldiers to aid in the fight."
msgstr ""
"\"Un commandant est défait. J'avais espéré gagner un nouvel allié, mais "
"priver Eldred de ses forces et gagner du temps, c'est déjà ça. Et maintenant "
"que ce donjon est à nous, je peux recruter plus de troupes pour continuer le "
"combat."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:779
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"One leader is defeated. I had hoped to gain a new ally, but depriving Eldred "
"and buying time is good enough."
msgstr ""
"Un chef est vaincu. J'espérais gagner un nouvel allié, mais priver Eldred de "
"son concours et gagner du temps me suffit amplement."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:784
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I should remember — soldiers I evacuate east will be available to fight "
"Eldred later, but if I evacuate too many I will be too weak to fight "
"effectively here!"
msgstr ""
"Je dois me rappeler que les soldats que j'évacue vers l'est pourront "
"combattre Eldred plus tard, mais que si j'évacue trop de monde, je serai "
"trop affaibli pour mener le combat efficacement ici !"

#. [message]
#. tell the player that this isn't the entirety of Wesnoth’s army. Even if the player defeats most of them here, Eldred will still have a big army in the next (and final) scenario.
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:794
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Deoran’s putting up a real fight! But even if he defeats me, he’ll never get "
"back into Wesnoth — we still have soldiers encamped on the southern shore."
msgstr ""
"Deoran se défend avec acharnement ! Mais même s'il me bat, il ne retournera "
"jamais à Wesnoth — nous avons encore des soldats campés sur la côte sud."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:808
#, fuzzy
msgid "So much ill will... The captains of old would have died for their king."
msgstr ""
"Que de malveillance... Les capitaines d’autrefois auraient sacrifié leur vie "
"pour leur roi."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:812
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Perhaps it is not a coincidence that so many of the old guard fell in battle "
"against the orcs."
msgstr ""
"Peut-être n'est-ce pas une coïncidence si tant de vétérans de la vieille "
"garde soient tombés au combat contre les orcs."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:823
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You are defeated, mage! Lend me your ear and hear the truth about Garard’s "
"death! ’twas not I who struck the blow, but Prince Eldred!"
msgstr ""
"Tu es vaincu, mage ! Prête-moi l'oreille et entends la vérité sur la mort de "
"Garard ! Ce n'est pas moi qui ai porté le coup, mais le prince Eldred !"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. said by a male Red Mage or Silver Mage
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:828
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I’m not stupid, Deoran; I’ve heard the whispers about how Asheviere is "
"raising her son. But isn’t it all for the best? Garard wasn’t going to give "
"up warmongering until we were all dead; at least this way maybe I can get "
"back to Alduin in one piece!"
msgstr ""
"Je ne suis pas idiot, Deoran ; j’ai entendu les rumeurs sur la façon dont "
"Asheviere élève son fils. Mais n’est-ce pas finalement un mal pour un bien ? "
"Garard n’allait pas renoncer à la guerre tant que nous ne serions pas tous "
"morts ; au moins, de cette façon, je pourrai peut-être retourner auprès à "
"Alduin sain et sauf !"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:834
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You care so little for the affairs of Wesnoth? Then go; lead your magi home, "
"and trouble the mainland no more."
msgstr ""
"Les affaires de Wesnoth vous importent si peu ? Alors partez ; ramenez vos "
"mages chez eux et cessez de troubler le continent."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:839
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You care so little for the affairs of Wesnoth? Then go; return home to "
"Alduin, and trouble the mainland no more."
msgstr ""
"Les affaires de Wesnoth vous importent si peu ? Alors partez ; retournez "
"chez vous, à Alduin, et cessez de troubler le continent."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. said by a male Shock Trooper
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:860
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"(<i>spits</i>) Traitor. Kill me if you must, but I will never betray my "
"country."
msgstr ""
"(<i>crache</i>) Traître. Tuez-moi si vous le devez, mais je ne trahirai "
"jamais mon pays."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:864
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"My comrade-in-arms, you already have. Look around! Eldred commands you to "
"fight and die on his behalf, while he himself has fled the battlefield.\n"
"\n"
"Are these the actions of an orphaned son, filled with a righteous desire for "
"vengeance? Or is this a scheming usurper, pitting his kingdom against itself "
"while he watches from a safe distance?"
msgstr ""
"Mon camarade d'armes, tu l'as déjà fait. Regarde autour de toi ! Eldred "
"t'ordonne de combattre et de mourir pour lui, alors que lui-même a fui le "
"champ de bataille.\n"
"\n"
"Est-ce là l'acte d'un fils orphelin, animé d'un juste désir de vengeance ? "
"Ou bien celui d'un usurpateur machiavélique, semant la discorde dans son "
"royaume tout en observant la situation à distance ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:870
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You know me, Sir Grey; we have fought side by side for many years now. Do "
"you truly believe that I would conspire with Delfador to assassinate the "
"king?"
msgstr ""
"Vous me connaissez, messire Grey ; nous avons combattu côte à côte pendant "
"de nombreuses années. Croyez-vous vraiment que je conspirerais avec Delfador "
"pour assassiner le roi ?"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. said by a male Shock Trooper
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:876
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I <i>thought</i> I knew you... I’m just not sure anymore. Who speaks the "
"truth? Maybe I need to get back to Dan’Tonk, away from all this fighting, "
"and take time to think. Men, let’s get out of here!"
msgstr ""
"Je <i>croyais</i> te connaître… Mais je n’en suis plus si sûr. Qui dit la "
"vérité ? Peut-être devrais-je retourner à Dan’Tonk, loin de toute cette "
"agitation, et prendre le temps de réfléchir. Allez, les gars, filons d’ici !"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. said by a male Shock Trooper
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:882
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I <i>thought</i> I knew you... I’m just not sure anymore. Who speaks the "
"truth? Maybe I need to get back to Dan’Tonk, away from all this fighting, "
"and take time to think."
msgstr ""
"Je <i>croyais</i> te connaître... mais je ne suis plus sûr de rien. Qui dit "
"la vérité ? Peut-être devrais-je retourner à Dan’Tonk, loin de tout ces "
"combats, et prendre le temps de réfléchir."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:900
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Colonel! You’re a man of experience, and a man of wisdom. Do you not care "
"for your king? Do you truly believe that it was by my hand he fell?"
msgstr ""
"Colonel ! Vous êtes un homme d'expérience et de sagesse. N'avez-vous donc "
"aucune affection pour votre roi ? Croyez-vous vraiment que c'est ma main qui "
"l'a tué ?"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. said by a male General
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:905
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I cared for Garard, but I care even more for the soldiers and common folk of "
"Wesnoth, folk who have just been plunged into civil war."
msgstr ""
"J'avais de l'affection pour Garard, mais j'ai encore plus d'affection pour "
"les soldats et les gens du peuple de Wesnoth, des gens qui viennent d'être "
"plongés dans la guerre civile."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. said by a male General
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:910
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Whether the deed was done by your hand or Eldred’s, it is my duty as a "
"commander to end the fighting as swiftly as possible. And that means "
"crushing your revolt."
msgstr ""
"Que cet acte soit de votre main ou de celle d'Eldred, il est de mon devoir "
"de commandant de mettre fin aux combats au plus vite. Et cela implique "
"d'écraser votre révolte."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:914
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You poor fool... can you not guess what horrors will come with a kin-slayer "
"on the throne? Sometimes we must fight not just for the people of today, but "
"for the people who will come after."
msgstr ""
"Pauvre fou… ne peux-tu donc imaginer les horreurs qui accompagneront un "
"parricide sur le trône ? Parfois, nous devons nous battre non seulement pour "
"les générations actuelles, mais aussi pour les générations futures."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:918
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I should finish you off, but your heart is in the right place. I cannot bear "
"to slay a righteous man. Begone."
msgstr ""
"Je devrais t'achever, mais tes intentions sont bonnes. Je ne peux me "
"résoudre à tuer un homme juste. Va-t'en."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:936
#, fuzzy
msgid "You—"
msgstr "Vous—"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. said by a male Shock Trooper
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:941
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Don’t even start. Garard dragged me away from my life of luxury to be an "
"officer in his lousy war. I always wanted him dead, and I’m glad someone "
"finally built up the courage to do it."
msgstr ""
"N'en parlons même pas. Garard m'a arraché à ma vie de luxe pour devenir "
"officier dans sa guerre minable. J'ai toujours souhaité sa mort, et je suis "
"heureux que quelqu'un ait enfin eu le courage de la commettre."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. said by a male Shock Trooper
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:946
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Kill me if you must, but I’ll never condemn the prince’s actions. From what "
"I hear, Garard was a pretty lousy father and husband too. Now am I free to "
"go, or not?"
msgstr ""
"Tuez-moi si vous voulez, mais je ne condamnerai jamais les actes du prince. "
"D'après ce que j'ai entendu, Garard était un piètre père et un assez mauvais "
"mari. Suis-je libre de partir maintenant, ou non ?"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. said by a male Shock Trooper
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:955
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"That’s what I thought. Now get out of my way — my men and I are going back "
"home to Weldyn."
msgstr ""
"C’est bien ce que je pensais. Maintenant, écartez-vous de mon chemin ! Mes "
"hommes et moi rentrons chez nous, à Weldyn."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:973
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Your sword has failed you, knight of Wesnoth! Now use your ears instead, and "
"hear the truth about our King Garard’s death!"
msgstr ""
"Ta lame t'a trahi, chevalier de Wesnoth ! Maintenant, utilise tes oreilles à "
"la place, et écoute la vérité sur la mort de notre roi Garard !"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. said by a male Swordsman
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:978
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Spare me the theatrics, Deoran. I know Eldred’s the one who took down the "
"old tyrant."
msgstr ""
"Épargne-moi tes simagrées, Deoran. Je sais que c’est Eldred qui a mis fin au "
"règne de l’ancien tyran."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. said by a male Swordsman
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:983
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"But gold is gold, and the prince has offered my wife and me a whole lot of "
"it to stick with the “official” story.\n"
"\n"
"Prince Eldred knows how to reward his allies. Give up now, accept the blame, "
"and he might even let you spend the rest of your days back in exile instead "
"of prison."
msgstr ""
"Mais l'or, c'est l'or, et le prince nous en a offert une grande quantité à "
"ma femme et à moi pour soutenir la version ‘officielle’.\n"
"\n"
"Le prince Eldred sait récompenser ses alliés. Abandonne maintenant, endosse "
"la culpabilité, et il te permettra peut-être de passer le reste de tes jours "
"en exil plutôt qu'en prison.\""

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:989
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Garard was no hero, but you, soldier, are a villain. May your heirs prove "
"wiser than you were."
msgstr ""
"Garard n'était peut-être pas un héros, mais toi, soldat, tu es un vrai "
"méchant. Puissent tes héritiers être plus sages que tu ne l'as été."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. said by a male Master Bowman
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1008
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Wait, please don’t kill me Deoran! I know that you would never betray "
"Garard, but what do you expect me to do about it!? If even the king can be "
"killed, what hope do I have if I speak up?"
msgstr ""
"Attends, Deoran, ne me tue pas ! Je sais que tu n’aurais jamais trahi "
"Garard, mais que veux-tu que j'y fasse ?! Si même le roi peut être tué, quel "
"espoir puis-je avoir si je parle ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1012
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Then stand alongside me, and we will fight together for the truth! Eldred’s "
"lies cannot be allowed to spread."
msgstr ""
"Alors tiens-toi à mes côtés, et nous lutterons ensemble pour la vérité ! On "
"ne doit pas laisser se propager les mensonges d'Eldred."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. said by a male Master Bowman
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1017
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Fighting together with you didn’t do the king much good, did it? No, my "
"company and I are getting back to Tath while we still have the chance!"
msgstr ""
"Se battre à tes côtés n'a pas vraiment été bénéfique pour le roi, n'est-ce "
"pas ? Non, moi et mes compagnons, on rentre à Tath tant que l'on peut "
"encore !"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1034
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Stand down! Hold your sword and hear me out! By the very Sceptre itself, I "
"swear I did not kill the king!"
msgstr ""
"Arrêtez-vous ! Abaissez votre épée et écoutez-moi ! Par le sceptre lui-même, "
"je jure que je n'ai pas tué le roi !"

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. said by a male Duelist
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1039
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Wait, what!? King Garard is dead!? I heard a commotion in camp and sent my "
"fighters to help — how did the king die? What are you doing here?"
msgstr ""
"Quoi !? Le roi Garard est mort !? J'ai entendu du raffut dans le camp, alors "
"j'ai envoyé mes troupes prêter main-forte — comment est-il mort, le roi ? Et "
"qu'est-ce que vous faites ici ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1043
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Your ignorance is truly a relief to hear, for Prince Eldred has slain the "
"king, and blamed me for the fell deed! I have been fighting most fiercely "
"against Eldred and his allies. If you are in any shape to help, I could "
"sorely use your aid."
msgstr ""
"Votre ignorance est un véritable soulagement, car le prince Eldred a tué le "
"roi et m'accuse de ce crime ! Je lutte avec acharnement contre Eldred et ses "
"alliés. Si vous êtes en mesure de m'aider, votre soutien me serait précieux."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#. said by a male Duelist
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1048
#, fuzzy
msgid "I— yes, of course! Anything I can do."
msgstr "Moi… oui, bien sûr ! Tout ce que je peux faire."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1068
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"That’s the last of the leaders. Eldred has been deprived of his entire "
"northern force! Well done, well done all!"
msgstr ""
"Voilà le dernier des chefs. Eldred est privé de toutes les forces du Nord ! "
"Bravo à tous !"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1073
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"All that now remains is for us to hold as long as possible, and be a "
"nuisance to Eldred’s orcish allies! The longer we survive, the longer "
"Delfador will have to prepare!"
msgstr ""
"Il ne nous reste plus qu'à tenir le plus longtemps possible et à importuner "
"les alliés orcs d'Eldred ! Plus longtemps nous survivrons, plus Delfador "
"aura de temps pour se préparer !"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1081
#, fuzzy
msgid "Survive as long as possible (bonus gold next scenario)."
msgstr "Survivre le plus longtemps possible (bonus d'or au prochain scénario)."

#. [message]: speaker=Ghuvog
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1148
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You’d better keep your human-queen’s promise of tribute, worms! Chief Ghuvog "
"is not cheap to buy; you swore to me that Fort Garard would burn to the "
"ground!"
msgstr ""
"Vous feriez bien de tenir la promesse de votre reine humaine concernant le "
"tribut, vermissaux ! Le chef Ghuvog n’est pas facile à acheter ; vous m’avez "
"juré que le Fort Garard brûlerait jusqu’au sol"

#. [message]: role=ghuvog_friend
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1152
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Yeah, I want revenge for our defeat and humiliation! It’s time for heads to "
"roll!"
msgstr ""
"Oui, je veux qu’on se venge de notre défaite et de notre humiliation ! Il "
"est temps que des têtes roulent !"

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1156
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"<i><b>Just</b></i> the rebels, beast — remember our deal. Pledge enough "
"warriors into my service and you shall be rewarded most generously once "
"Mother and I have consolidated our control."
msgstr ""
"<i><b>Uniquement</b></i> les rebelles, gougnafier — souviens-toi de notre "
"accord. Engage suffisamment de guerriers à mon service et tu seras "
"généreusement récompensé une fois que Mère et moi aurons consolidé notre "
"pouvoir."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1204
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Eldred has betrayed Wesnoth’s strife to the orcish clans. With grunts "
"swarming along the riverbank, the road east to Delfador is no longer safe. "
"There can be no more escape."
msgstr ""
"Eldred a trahi les intérêts de Wesnoth vis à vis des clans orques. Avec des "
"grognements résonnant sur les rives du fleuve, la route à l'est vers "
"Delfador n'est plus sûre. Désormais il n'y a plus d'échappatoire."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1209
#, fuzzy
msgid "The orcs are back! There’s hordes of them!"
msgstr "Les orcs sont de retour ! Il y a toute une horde !"

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1213
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"At ease, soldier. We’ve made a deal. They’re here to help us fight the "
"rebels."
msgstr ""
"Du calme, soldat. Nous avons conclu un accord. Ils sont là pour nous aider à "
"combattre les rebelles."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1218
#, fuzzy
msgid "We’re working with orcs? But, your father—"
msgstr "Nous collaborons avec les orcs ? Mais, votre père…"

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1222
#, fuzzy
msgid "My father is <i><b>dead</b></i>, soldier. Let the beasts through."
msgstr "Mon père est <i><b>mort</b></i>, soldat. Laissez passer ces rustauds."

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1232
#, fuzzy
msgid "Defeat as many enemy leaders as possible (bonus gold next scenario)."
msgstr ""
"Vaincre autant de chefs ennemis que possible (bonus d'or au prochain "
"scénario)."

#. [message]
#. "trog" is a made-up slur referring to an orc
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1271
#, fuzzy
msgid "Filthy trog. I don’t trust you, whatever Eldred says."
msgstr ""
"Sale troglo. Je ne te fais pas confiance, peu importe ce qu'Eldred en dit."

#. [message]: speaker=unit
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1275
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You’re lucky your boss is paying us off, weakling. We’ve free reign to "
"pillage any town that resists his rule, so keep your mouth shut or your home "
"will be next."
msgstr ""
"Tu as de la chance que ton patron nous corrompe, pauvre type. On a carte "
"blanche pour piller n'importe quelle ville qui résiste à son autorité, alors "
"ferme-la ou ta maison sera la prochaine."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1342
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Agony! My arm goes limp, I can fight no longer. Any allies yet standing, "
"scatter, scatter to the hills! It is me they will chase, not you."
msgstr ""
"C'est l'Agonie ! Mon bras me lâche, je ne peux plus continuer à me battre. À "
"tous ceux qui tiennent encore, fuyez, fuyez vers les collines ! C’est moi "
"qu’ils traqueront, pas vous."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1346
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"And as for me, well, I may have cut things rather closer than I had planned. "
"But what’s done is done — my thoughts must now turn to flight. Make haste, "
"my loyal steed!"
msgstr ""
"Quant à moi, eh bien, il semble que j'aie joué avec le feu un plus que "
"prévu. Mais ce qui est fait est fait — il est temps de penser à s'enfuir. "
"Hâte-toi, mon fidèle destrier !"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1351
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Agony! My arm goes limp, I can fight no longer. This may be cutting things "
"rather closer than I had planned, but what’s done is done."
msgstr ""
"Aïe ! Mon bras est inerte, je ne peux plus me battre. Il semble que j'aie "
"joué avec le feu un plus que prévu, mais ce qui est fait est fait."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1355
#, fuzzy
msgid "My thoughts must now turn to flight: make haste, my loyal steed!"
msgstr ""
"Mes pensées doivent maintenant se tourner vers la fuite : hâte-toi, mon "
"fidèle destrier !"

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1398
#, fuzzy
msgid "(grins)"
msgstr "(sourire)"

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1403
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Well, well, if it isn’t Deoran the exile, one-time commander of the South "
"Guard; a soldier to the very end. I’ve heard all about you, you know. A "
"perfect example of who not to be."
msgstr ""
"Tiens, tiens, si ce n'est pas Deoran l'exilé, ancien commandant de la Garde "
"Sud ; un soldat jusqu'au bout. J'ai tout entendu sur toi, tu sais. Un "
"parfait exemple de ce qu'il ne faut pas devenir."

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#. "black bottle" foreshadowing
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1408
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Did you really think you could win? Even if you had bested my army — yes, "
"it’s <b><i>my</i></b> army now — I now carry with me so much magic that I’ll "
"never have to lose another fight."
msgstr ""
"Pensais-tu vraiment pouvoir l’emporter ? Même si tu avais vaincu mon armée — "
"oui, c’est bien mon armée maintenant —, je porte en moi tellement de magie "
"que je ne perdrai plus jamais un combat."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1413
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"At last the usurper dares to face me, now that I am too injured for battle. "
"He knows his actions are unforgivable. He knows he cannot face me in a fair "
"fight."
msgstr ""
"Enfin, l’usurpateur a le courage de se présenter face à moi, maintenant que "
"je suis trop affaibli pour me défendre. Il sait que ce qu'il a fait est "
"impardonnable. Il sait qu'il ne peut pas m’affronter dans une lutte "
"équitable."

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1417
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I also know you’re a man of your word, so I’m going to give you a choice. "
"You can surrender, leave Wesnoth, and swear to never again raise arms up "
"against my rule."
msgstr ""
"Je sais aussi que tu es un homme de parole, alors je vais te donner le "
"choix. Tu peux te rendre, quitter Wesnoth, et jurer de ne jamais plus lever "
"les armes contre mon autorité."

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1421
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Or you can fight, die, and have your corpse hoisted upon the walls of Weldyn "
"as a warning to others. Which will it be, exile?"
msgstr ""
"Ou tu peux te battre, mourir, et voir ton cadavre hissé sur les murs de "
"Weldyn comme avertissement pour les autres. Que choisis-tu, exilé ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1425
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"More than anything does my spirit yearn to go on fighting, to risk it all on "
"a chance at vanquishing the one responsible for all this wretched "
"destruction!"
msgstr ""
"Plus que tout, mon esprit aspire à continuer à se battre, à tout risquer "
"pour avoir une chance de vaincre celui qui a engendré toute cette "
"destruction abominable !"

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1429
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"But my heart remembers better places, happier times. There are... people I "
"wish to speak to, things I have left unsaid..."
msgstr ""
"Mais mon cœur garde en mémoire de meilleurs souvenirs, des instants plus "
"heureux. Il y a… des gens avec qui je voudrais parler, des choses que je "
"n’ai pas eu l’occasion de dire..."

#. [message]: speaker=Deoran
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1433
#, fuzzy
msgid "Prince Eldred, I lay down my arms and accept your offer of surrender."
msgstr ""
"Prince Eldred, je dépose les armes et j'accepte votre offre de reddition."

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1456
#, fuzzy
msgid "Idiot."
msgstr "Idiot"

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1464
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Not a deceitful bone in his body. I didn’t even have to drink the potion. "
"That’s... a relief."
msgstr ""
"Aucune malhonnêteté en lui. Je n'ai même pas eu besoin de boire la potion. "
"C’est... un soulagement."

#. [message]: speaker=Kestrel
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1468
#, fuzzy
msgid "The traitor is vanquished! Now hail, hail to your new king!"
msgstr "Le traître est vaincu ! Maintenant, vive, vive votre nouveau roi !"

#. [message]: id=$speaker1_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1482
#, fuzzy
msgid "Hail King Eldred!"
msgstr "Vive le roi Eldred!"

#. [message]: id=$speaker2_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1493
#, fuzzy
msgid "Hail, long live King Eldred!"
msgstr "Longue vie au roi Eldred !"

#. [message]: id=$speaker3_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1504
#, fuzzy
msgid "Long live the king!"
msgstr "Que vive le roi !"

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13_Revelry_Revisited.cfg:1512
#, fuzzy
msgid "Yes. Long live the king."
msgstr "Oui. Longue vie au roi."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13x_The_King_is_Dead.cfg:4
#, fuzzy
msgid "The King is Dead"
msgstr "Le roi est mort"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13x_The_King_is_Dead.cfg:110
#, fuzzy
msgid "Gods... what a fool I have been."
msgstr "Mon Dieu... quel benêt ai-je été."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13x_The_King_is_Dead.cfg:115
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Whitefangs, Blackcrests. Saurians, Arand. I really thought I was doing "
"something great; fighting the good fight for king and country."
msgstr ""
"Crocs-blancs, Crêtes-noires. Sauriens, Arand. Je pensais vraiment faire "
"quelque chose de formidable ; menant le bon combat pour le roi et la patrie."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13x_The_King_is_Dead.cfg:119
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"But when it really mattered, I couldn’t see past my own ego. What kind of "
"man was I? What kind of <b><i>friend</i></b> was I?"
msgstr ""
"Mais quand cela comptait vraiment, je n'ai pas su voir au-delà de mon propre "
"ego. Quel genre d'homme ai-je été? Quel genre d'<b><i>ami</i></b> ai-je été ?"

#. [message]: speaker=$horselord_id
#. said by a male Horseman-line or Cavalryman-line unit
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13x_The_King_is_Dead.cfg:124
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"’tis a dark day indeed. Orcs rampage across the countryside, pillaging and "
"looting, while the false King Eldred does nothing. Worse than nothing: he "
"marches on our own settlements, consolidating his power!"
msgstr ""
"C'est en effet un jour sombre. Les orcs ravagent la campagne, pillent et "
"détroussent, tandis que le faux roi Eldred ne fait rien. Pire encore : il "
"marche contre nos propres terres, pour consolider son pouvoir !"

#. [message]: speaker=$horselord_id
#. said by a male Horseman-line or Cavalryman-line unit
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13x_The_King_is_Dead.cfg:129
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Our king has perished, our kingdom in peril! Are we to stand idly by and "
"watch it fall, o’ great Delfador?"
msgstr ""
"Notre roi a péri, notre royaume est en péril ! Allons-nous rester les bras "
"croisés et le laisser sombrer, ô grand Delfador ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#. $horselord_name is a male Horseman-line or Cavalryman-line unit
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13x_The_King_is_Dead.cfg:135
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I’m not “The Great” anymore, $horselord_name. Was I ever? Everything I ever "
"achieved was either a lie or has already been undone."
msgstr ""
"Je ne suis plus 'Le Grand Delfador' maintenant, $horselord_name. L'ai-je "
"jamais été ? Tout ce que j'ai réalisé n'était qu'un tissu de mensonges, ou a "
"déjà été détruit."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13x_The_King_is_Dead.cfg:139
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Our company is strong, but what power have we to lay low the walls of "
"Weldyn? To wreak fire and lightning through the streets until finally I "
"excise the festering boil at the heart of all this madness? If only."
msgstr ""
"Notre compagnie est forte, mais quel puissance avons-nous pour abattre les "
"murs de Weldyn ? Pour semer le feu et la foudre dans les rues, jusqu'à ce "
"que j'extirpe ce furoncle purulent au cœur de toute cette folie ? Si "
"seulement."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13x_The_King_is_Dead.cfg:145
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I was warned about this... <i>“Bestow not destruction, but the gleaming "
"light of truth instead”</i>; <i>“the line of kings sundered”</i> — what can "
"the seer have been referring to if not my attack on Arand?\n"
"\n"
"Even now, still I understand nothing! <i>“From the barren throne will rise "
"an angel of ashes”</i> — <i>“The nameless son and the ashen daughter”</i> — "
"what nightmares are these that are prophesied to arise from my failure? The "
"coming years will be dark indeed."
msgstr ""
"J'ai été averti de cela... <i>“Ne dispense pas la destruction, mais la "
"lumière éclatante de la vérité à la place”</i>; <i>“la lignée des rois "
"brisée”</i> — à quoi la devineresse faisait-elle allusion si ce n'est à mon "
"attaque contre Arand ?\n"
"\n"
"Même maintenant, je ne comprends toujours rien ! <i>“Du trône désert naîtra "
"un ange de cendres”</i> — <i>“Le fils sans nom et la fille de cendres”</i> — "
"quels cauchemars ces prophéties annoncent-elles, nées de mon échec ? Les "
"années à venir seront vraiment sombres."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13x_The_King_is_Dead.cfg:151
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Oh seer, what I would give for another chance! I obeyed my friend, and in "
"doing so betrayed him! And now there is nothing left."
msgstr ""
"Ô devineresse, ce que je donnerais pour une nouvelle chance ! J'ai obéi à "
"mon ami, et ce faisant, je l'ai trahi ! Et maintenant, il ne reste plus rien."

#. [message]: speaker=Methor
#. "no need to be so glum" is what Delfador says in S01
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13x_The_King_is_Dead.cfg:167
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Delfador, I have found you at last! “Nothing left?” There’s no need to be so "
"glum."
msgstr ""
"Delfador, je t'ai enfin déniché ! « Il n'y a plus rien ? » il n’y pas de "
"raisons d’être aussi abattu."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13x_The_King_is_Dead.cfg:171
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Master!? I’d no idea you survived the coup! But you come far too late. I "
"fear it’s all already over."
msgstr ""
"Maître !? Je ne savais pas que vous aviez survécu au coup d'État ! Mais vous "
"arrivez bien trop tard. Je crains que tout ne soit déjà fini."

#. [message]: speaker=Methor
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13x_The_King_is_Dead.cfg:176
#, fuzzy
msgid "I heard your earlier words to the horselord. Do not think of giving up!"
msgstr ""
"J'ai entendu ce que tu as dit au connétable. N’envisage même pas de "
"renoncer !\""

#. [message]: speaker=Methor
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13x_The_King_is_Dead.cfg:180
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The boy I raised always sought the approval of others: from your peers, from "
"your master, from your king. Now the darkness rings close, and at last you "
"are alone — even I have grown old, and can speak for you no longer."
msgstr ""
"Le garçon que j'ai éduqué a toujours cherché l'approbation des autres : de "
"ses pairs, de son maître, de son roi. Maintenant, les ténèbres se "
"rapprochent, et tu es enfin seul — même moi, j'ai vieilli, et je ne peux "
"plus parler pour toi."

#. [message]: speaker=Methor
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13x_The_King_is_Dead.cfg:184
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The time has come to choose. Who are you, Delfador? Are you nobody; a tired "
"young student; a hanger-on fawning at the feet of his betters? Or are you "
"Delfador the Great, no-one’s servant and his own man! CHOOSE, apprentice!"
msgstr ""
"Le moment est venu de faire un choix. Qui es-tu, Delfador ? N'es-tu "
"personne ; un jeune étudiant épuisé ; un suiveur se vautrant aux pieds de "
"ses supérieurs ? Ou es-tu Delfador le Grand, le serviteur de personne mais "
"le maître de sa destinée ! CHOISIS, apprenti !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13x_The_King_is_Dead.cfg:188
#, fuzzy
msgid "Look, Methor, it’s not as easy as saying a few words..."
msgstr ""
"Tu vois, Methor, ce n'est pas aussi simple que de dire quelques paroles..."

#. [message]: speaker=$horselord_id
#. said by a male Horseman-line or Cavalryman-line unit
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13x_The_King_is_Dead.cfg:210
#, fuzzy
msgid "Well? Shall we fight?"
msgstr "Alors ? On se bat ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13x_The_King_is_Dead.cfg:220
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"We shall fight! The usurper Eldred is on the march, and on the march he is "
"exposed. This time, we need no king nor country to guide our hand. I know "
"what is right, and I will make it so."
msgstr ""
"On va se battre ! L'usurpateur Eldred est en marche, et pendant sa marche il "
"est vulnérable. Cette fois, ni roi ni nation ne guideront nos actions. Je "
"sais ce qui est juste, et je ferai en sorte que cela se réalise."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13x_The_King_is_Dead.cfg:224
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Scouts, take my seal! Spread the word: all of Wesnoth must know of Eldred’s "
"treachery. Whether it takes one year or a hundred, I <b><i>will</i></b> see "
"the throne of Wesnoth restored."
msgstr ""
"Éclaireurs, prenez mon sceau ! Diffusez la nouvelle : tout Wesnoth doit "
"connaître la trahison d'Eldred. Qu'il faille un an ou cent ans, je "
"<b><i>ferai</i></b> restaurer le trône de Wesnoth."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/13x_The_King_is_Dead.cfg:228
#, fuzzy
msgid "The rest of you, make ready! We march to kill the king."
msgstr "Vous autres, préparez-vous ! Nous marchons pour tuer le roi."

#. [scenario]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:4
#, fuzzy
msgid "Long Live the Queen"
msgstr "Longue vie à la Reine"

#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:22
#, fuzzy
msgid "Delfador’s Rebels"
msgstr "Rebelles de Delfador"

#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:69
#, fuzzy
msgid "King Eldred"
msgstr "Roi Eldred"

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:227
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"A heroic duel, Delfador? Really? You forget that I have an army on my side."
msgstr ""
"Un duel héroïque, Delfador ? Vraiment ? Tu oublies que j'ai une armée de mon "
"côté."

#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:315
#, fuzzy
msgid "Foxtail Outriders"
msgstr "Les Cavaliers Queue-de-Renard"

#. [side]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:327
msgid "Blackcrest Outriders"
msgstr "Cavaliers des Crêtes-noires"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:560
#, fuzzy
msgid "No! Methor... Don’t die!"
msgstr "Non ! Methor... Ne meurs pas !"

#. [message]: speaker=Methor
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:564
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Delfador, my sweet, wonderful apprentice... I couldn’t be more proud of "
"you..."
msgstr ""
"Delfador, mon aimable et merveilleux apprenti... Je ne pourrais être plus "
"fièr de toi..."

#. [message]: speaker=Methor
#. callback to S01 where Methor complains about Delfador not learning a seeker spell
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:586
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Look at the length of that column! The prince — the king, I suppose — must "
"have picked up more soldiers at Dan’Tonk, when he forced the magistrate to "
"swear fealty. Your seeker spell was excellent, Delfador; we’ve been able to "
"find and intercept Eldred before he could turn anyone else to his cause."
msgstr ""
"Regardez la longueur de cette colonne ! Le prince — enfin, le roi, je "
"suppose — a dû recruter davantage de soldats à Dan'Tonk, lorsqu'il a forcé "
"le magistrat à prêter allégeance. Ton sort de recherche était excellent, "
"Delfador ; nous avons pu retrouver et intercepter Eldred avant qu'il n'en "
"rallie d'autres à sa cause."

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:590
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Boss, how’s we supposed to fight that many!? Even if we could, what about "
"Queen Asheviere back in Weldyn?"
msgstr ""
"Patron, comment est-on censé affronter autant de soldats !? Même si on "
"pouvait, que faire de la reine Asheviere à Weldyn ?"

#. [message]: speaker=$horselord_id
#. said by a male Horseman-line or Cavalryman-line unit
#. "reigns" is a pun - "reigns of power", but also the kind of reins that you use to control a horse (this is a mounted unit speaking)
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:596
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Indeed! Word is she’s killed half of the court and paid off the rest; the "
"remaining lords of the city are loyal only to her! Eldred may be king, but "
"Asheviere holds the reins."
msgstr ""
"En effet ! On dit qu'elle a tué la moitié de la cour et acheté le reste ; "
"les seigneurs restants de la ville lui seront loyaux à elle seule ! Eldred "
"est peut-être roi, mais c'est Asheviere qui tient les rênes."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:600
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"We don’t have to fight the entire army or deal with Weldyn. The capital is "
"too well-defended for us to sack outright — Eldred is the objective here."
msgstr ""
"Nous n’avons pas à affronter toute l’armée ni à nous occuper de Weldyn. La "
"capitale est trop bien défendue pour qu’on puisse la prendre de force — "
"Eldred est notre objectif ici."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:604
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Once the truth gets out about Garard’s death, we’ll have enough allies to "
"liberate Weldyn and more besides. But only if we can stop Eldred here and "
"now — can prove to the watchers that this coup is not yet over; that justice "
"and honor and hope still live in Wesnoth! That’s our goal today."
msgstr ""
"Une fois que la vérité sur la mort de Garard sera révélée, nous aurons assez "
"d'alliés pour libérer Weldyn et bien plus encore. Mais cela ne sera possible "
"que si nous arrêtons Eldred ici et maintenant — si nous prouvons aux "
"observateurs que ce coup d'État n'est pas encore terminé ; que la justice, "
"l'honneur et l'espoir sont toujours vivants à Wesnoth ! Voilà notre objectif "
"aujourd'hui."

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:609
#, fuzzy
msgid "Look sharp, I think they’ve spotted us!"
msgstr "Soyez vigilants, je crois qu'ils nous ont repérés !"

#. [message]: speaker=$companion_id
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:610
#, fuzzy
msgid "female^Look sharp, I think they’ve spotted us!"
msgstr "Soyez vigilants, je crois qu'ils nous ont repérés !"

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:618
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Delfador, welcome! I was wondering if we’d get an appearance from you old "
"has-been! ’fraid you’re not as popular with Mother and me as you were with "
"old Garard."
msgstr ""
"Delfador, bienvenue ! Je commençais à me demander si on aurait droit à une "
"apparition du vieux ! J'ai bien peur que tu ne sois plus aussi apprécié par "
"Mère et moi qu'à l'époque de Garard."

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:622
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Opposing me is hopeless, old mage. But it’s not too late to save yourself — "
"surrender now, disband your little rebel rabble, and we can tell the men it "
"was all a big misunderstanding."
msgstr ""
"Il est vain de vouloir s'opposer à moi, vieux mage. Mais il n'est pas trop "
"tard pour te sauver — rends-toi, disperse ton petit groupe de rebelles, et "
"nous pourrons expliquer aux hommes que ce n'était qu'un malentendu."

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:626
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Just lay down your staff and greet me with open arms. You can even have your "
"old title back! “Delfador the Great”, High Advisor to the Crown — don’t you "
"agree that has a nice ring to it?"
msgstr ""
"Dépose ton bâton et accueille-moi à bras ouverts. Tu peux même récupérer ton "
"ancien titre ! « Delfador le Grand », Haut Conseiller de la Couronne — tu ne "
"trouves pas que ça sonne bien ?"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:630
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I am no longer so foolish as to be tempted by <b><i>that</i></b>, young "
"prince! Enough blood has been spilled on your behalf; stop this madness and "
"give up the throne, or I shall make you."
msgstr ""
"Je ne suis plus assez naïf pour être tenté par <b><i>cela</i></b>, jeune "
"prince ! Assez de sang a été versé en ton nom ; arrête cette folie et "
"renonce au trône, ou je te forcerai à le faire."

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:634
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Oh no, I don’t think so. You forget you’re speaking to your king, old man. "
"Soldiers, attack! ATTACK!"
msgstr ""
"Oh non, je ne pense pas. Tu oublies que tu parles à ton roi, vieil homme. "
"Soldats, à l'attaque ! À l'attaque!"

#. [objective]: condition=win
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:644
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1036
#, fuzzy
msgid "Defeat Eldred"
msgstr "Vaincre Eldred"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:724
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Eldred, you know full well that your father and I were close! Is this what "
"he would have wanted? His kingdom turned against itself, his townships "
"pillaged by orcs? He had hope; a future for Wesnoth! A future for you!"
msgstr ""
"Eldred, tu sais parfaitement que ton père et moi étions proches ! Est-ce ce "
"qu'il aurait voulu ? Son royaume retourné contre lui, ses villes pillées par "
"des orcs ? Il avait de l'espoir ; un avenir pour Wesnoth ! Un avenir pour "
"toi !"

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:728
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"A future for me? I can count on one hand the times the old tyrant had "
"anything kind to say about me."
msgstr ""
"Un avenir pour moi ? Je peux compter sur une main les rares fois où le vieux "
"tyran a eu quelque chose de gentil à dire à mon égard."

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:732
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I wasn’t going to wait around to be disinherited, or worse. It was always "
"going to be him or me — I just beat him to the finish."
msgstr ""
"Je n’allais pas attendre d’être déshérité, ou pire. Ça a toujours été lui ou "
"moi — j’ai juste été plus rapide."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:736
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Fool. I will not bandy words with whatever madness has taken root inside "
"your mind, Eldred. Garard was harsh; I cannot deny that. But you’re a fool "
"if you think he ever felt anything but love for you."
msgstr ""
"Imbécile. Je ne vais pas perdre de temps à discuter avec la folie qui a pris "
"racine dans ton esprit, Eldred. Garard était dur, je ne peux pas le nier. "
"Mais tu es un imbécile si tu penses qu'il n'a jamais ressenti autre chose "
"que de l'amour pour toi."

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:743
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I’m no fool, Delfador. Day and night, my parents fought. Whether said in "
"truth or in anger, there are some things my father can never take back."
msgstr ""
"Je ne suis pas un imbécile, Delfador. Jour et nuit, mes parents se sont "
"affrontés. Qu’elles aient été dites avec sincérité ou avec colère, il y a "
"des choses que mon père ne pourra jamais effacer."

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:747
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"And don’t think that I have any illusions about what sort of snake Mother is "
"either. I know, believe me. But she’s the snake who’s made me king, and "
"that’s good enough."
msgstr ""
"\"Et ne crois pas que j'aie des illusions sur le genre de serpent qu’est "
"Mère. Je la connais, crois-moi. Mais c’est elle qui m’a fait roi, et ça "
"suffit à mon bonheur.\""

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#. this refers to the events of S05 The Deceiver and S06 Ring of Swords
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:759
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"This wasn’t the first time Mother’s gone after Garard, you know. In the "
"early days of the war, she betrayed his plans to the Whitefangs; fled to the "
"orcs while they surrounded you and him both."
msgstr ""
"Ce n’était pas la première fois que Mère s’en prenait à Garard, tu sais. Dès "
"le début de la guerre, elle a révélé ses plans aux Crocs-blancs ; elle a fui "
"vers les orcs pendant qu'ils vous encerclaient, toi et lui."

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:763
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You and Deoran brought her back, of course, and Lionel fought Garard free of "
"the orcs. My childhood would have been so different if things had "
"succeeded..."
msgstr ""
"Vous et Deoran l'avez ramenée, évidemment, et Lionel a libéré Garard des "
"orcs. Mon enfance aurait été bien différente si tout cela avait fonctionné..."

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:775
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I’m surprised you haven’t given up yet, wizard! But you’re no stranger to "
"hopeless fights, are you — you bested Malal, escaped the frozen north, "
"scattered our saurians."
msgstr ""
"Je suis surpris que tu n'aies pas encore abandonné, enchanteur ! Mais tu "
"n'es pas étranger aux combats sans espoir, n'est-ce pas — tu as vaincu "
"Malal, échappé au nord gelé, dispersé nos sauriens."

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:779
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Malal was clever; <i>really</i> clever, and determined too. No-one but "
"Mother knows what Garard did to earn Malal’s ire, but the two of them would "
"stop at nothing to see Garard dead and his reputation destroyed. Tricking "
"the saurians and orcs into working together, getting Lionel sent away, "
"pitting Garard against Arand..."
msgstr ""
"Malal était malin ; <i>vraiment</i> malin, et déterminé aussi. Personne, à "
"part Mère, ne sait ce que Garard a fait pour mériter la colère de Malal, "
"mais eux deux n'auraient rien épargné pour voir Garard mort et sa réputation "
"anéantie. Tromper les sauriens et les orcs pour les faire collaborer, faire "
"envoyer Lionel loin d’ici, opposer Garard à Arand..."

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:783
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Delfador, you weren’t supposed to survive Malal. You weren’t supposed to "
"survive <i><b>any</b></i> of that."
msgstr ""
"Delfador, tu n’étais pas censé survivre à Malal. Tu n’étais pas censé "
"survivre <i><b>à rien </b></i>de  tout cela."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:787
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Would that more had survived along with me, Eldred. Would that I had "
"listened to Deoran, would that I had understood the seer! Had I been but a "
"little wiser, so many lives might yet have been saved."
msgstr ""
"Si seulement davantage de gens avaient survécu avec moi, Eldred. Si j'avais "
"écouté Deoran, si j'avais compris les paroles de la devineresse ! Si j'avais "
"été un peu plus sage, tant de vies auraient pu être épargnées."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:791
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I can never atone for the lives I cost, but I can yet honor them through my "
"actions. And right now, honoring them means stopping you."
msgstr ""
"Je ne pourrai jamais expier les vies perdues à cause de moi, mais je peux "
"encore les honorer par mes actions. Et en ce moment, les honorer signifie "
"t'arrêter."

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:837
#, fuzzy
msgid "NO!"
msgstr "NON!"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:841
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"It’s over, Eldred. Down on your knees, now! The rest of you; get back! BACK, "
"or you’ll have to find yet another king!"
msgstr ""
"C’est fini, Eldred. À genoux, maintenant ! Vous autres, reculez ! RECULEZ, "
"sinon il vous faudra trouver un autre roi !"

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:845
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"I didn’t come all this way just to fail now... not at the hand of some cheap "
"conjurer. No, I prepared for this. After my failed attack on Arand, I "
"took... precautions."
msgstr ""
"\"Je ne suis pas arrivé jusque-là pour échouer maintenant... pas aux mains "
"d'un vulgaire prestidigitateur. Non, j'ai prévu le coup. Après mon attaque "
"ratée contre Arand, j'ai pris... des précautions."

#. [message]: speaker=Eldred
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:849
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"They say this elixir came all the way from the Old Continent, Delfador. "
"Persuading Malal to give it up wasn’t easy.\n"
"\n"
"You like magic so much? Once I drink from Jevyan’s Cup, I’ll have enough "
"magic to turn you all to dust!"
msgstr ""
"On dit que cet élixir vient tout droit de l’ancien continent, Delfador. "
"Persuader Malal de me le céder n'a pas été facile.\n"
"\n"
"Tu aimes tellement la magie ? Une fois que j'aurai bu dans la Coupe de "
"Jevyan, j'aurai assez de magie à ma disposition pour vous réduire tous en "
"poussière !\""

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#. liches are skeletal; they don't have blood. This is a consumable artifact of unknown composition, probably captured/extracted from lich-lord Jevyan
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:856
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Is that— are you holding <i>lich’s blood</i>!? How— Put it down, Eldred!"
msgstr ""
"Est-ce... est-ce que tu tiens du <i>sang de liche</i> !? Comment... Pose ça "
"immédiatement, Eldred !"

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:860
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Whatever you do, don’t you dare drink it! We have no idea what will happen! "
"Don’t you dare, Eldred! ELDRED!"
msgstr ""
"Quoi que tu fasses, ne bois surtout pas ça ! On n’a aucune idée de ce qui va "
"se passer ! Ne le fais pas, Eldred ! ELDRED !"

#. [unit]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:977
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1272
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1486
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1541
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1560
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/utils/unified_characters.cfg:94
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/utils/unified_characters.cfg:103
#, fuzzy
msgid "Eldred"
msgstr "Eldred"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1003
#, fuzzy
msgid "Finally, I understand."
msgstr "Enfin, je comprends."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1007
#, fuzzy
msgid "I can make the pain all go away. I can make everything better again."
msgstr "Je peux faire disparaître toute douleur. Je peux tout arranger."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1012
#, fuzzy
msgid "...you can?"
msgstr "...tu peux?"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1024
#, fuzzy
msgid "I just need to kill everyone else first."
msgstr "Je dois juste tuer tous les autres en premier."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1062
#, fuzzy
msgid "Everything is so clear now. I see the past; the future."
msgstr "Tout est si clair maintenant. Je vois le passé ; l'avenir."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1066
#, fuzzy
msgid "Your eyes were clouded. You could not tell the truth from the lie."
msgstr ""
"Vos yeux étaient voilés. Vous ne pouviez plus distinguer le vrai du faux."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1072
#, fuzzy
msgid "You still can’t, can you?"
msgstr "tu ne peux toujours pas, n'est-ce pas ?"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1245
#, fuzzy
msgid "Give up."
msgstr "Abandonne."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1369
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Your achievements are undone. Your king is dead. The ghosts of the past will "
"always haunt you, Delfador war-mage."
msgstr ""
"Tout ce que tu as accompli est réduit à néant. Ton roi est mort. Les "
"fantômes du passé te hanteront à jamais, Delfador, mage de guerre."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1501
#, fuzzy
msgid "No."
msgstr "Non."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1535
#, fuzzy
msgid "You really still don’t understand, do you?"
msgstr "Tu ne comprends toujours pas, n'est-ce pas ?"

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1552
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You had your chance to change fate. Your revelation came too late. The "
"future is already written."
msgstr ""
"Tu as eu l'occasion de changer le destin. Ta révélation est arrivée trop "
"tard. L'avenir est déjà écrit."

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#. prophecy callback
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1574
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"You have no title, no country, no king. You are a failure. Alone, you are "
"nothing."
msgstr "Tu n'as ni titre, ni pays, ni roi. Tu es un raté. Seul, tu n'es rien."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1634
#, fuzzy
msgid "Nothing? I am Delfador."
msgstr "Rien ? Je suis Delfador."

#. [message]: speaker=Delfador
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1638
#, fuzzy
msgid "And you are dust."
msgstr "Et tu n'es que poussière."

#. [message]
#. 13 kings is made-up, because 13 is an unlucky number. 12 non-Eldred kings across 500 years makes for an average 42 year reign
#. given Wesnoth's access to magical healing, a 42-year reign average seems plausible, if rather high.
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1659
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Thus perishes Eldred, thirteenth king of Wesnoth.\n"
"\n"
"With him ends the story of the sons of Haldric; that unbroken line of kings "
"stretching five hundred years back to the Green Isle itself."
msgstr ""
"Ainsi périt Eldred, treizième roi de Wesnoth.\n"
"\n"
"Avec lui s'achève l'histoire des fils d'Haldric, cette lignée royale "
"ininterrompue remontant à cinq cents ans jusqu'à l'Île Verte."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1665
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The exhausted Delfador fights valiantly against Eldred’s — now Asheviere’s — "
"army, but reinforcements from Weldyn eventually repulse the beleaguered "
"rebels. Neither side wins a decisive military victory."
msgstr ""
"Épuisé, Delfador combattit vaillamment l'armée d'Eldred, désormais commandée "
"par Asheviere, mais les renforts venus de Weldyn finirent par repousser les "
"rebelles assiégés. Aucun des deux camps ne remporta de victoire militaire "
"décisive."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1669
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"As word spreads of the kings’ deaths, a terrible foreboding seems to settle "
"over the Wesnothian countryside."
msgstr ""
"À mesure que la nouvelle de la mort des rois se répandit, un terrible "
"pressentiment sembla s'abattre sur la campagne de Wesnoth."

#. [message]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/scenarios/14_Long_Live_the_Queen.cfg:1673
#, fuzzy
msgid "After all, the civil war has only just begun..."
msgstr "Après tout, la guerre civile ne faisait que commencer..."

#. [unit_type]: id=Cave Entrance, race=mechanical
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Cave_Entrance.cfg:5
#, fuzzy
msgid "Cave Entrance"
msgstr "Entrée de la caverne"

#. [unit_type]: id=Cave Entrance, race=mechanical
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Cave_Entrance.cfg:15
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"A crudely hewn passage into the earth, propped open by ageing wooden "
"supports."
msgstr ""
"Un passage grossièrement creusé dans la terre, maintenu ouvert par de vieux "
"supports en bois."

#. [unit_type]: id=Prince of Wesnoth, race=human, gender=male
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Arand.cfg:4
#, fuzzy
msgid "Prince of Wesnoth"
msgstr "Prince de Wesnoth"

#. [unit_type]: id=Prince of Wesnoth, race=human, gender=male
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Arand.cfg:14
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Brothers of a ruling king are traditionally titled ‘Prince’ and bequeathed "
"wide swathes of land to rule."
msgstr ""
"Les frères d'un roi régnant portent traditionnellement le titre de "
"« prince » et reçoivent en apanage de vastes étendues de terres à gouverner."

#. [attack]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Arand.cfg:28
#, fuzzy
msgid "broadsword"
msgstr "sabre"

#. [unit_type]: id=Queen, race=human, gender=female
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Asheviere.cfg:4
#, fuzzy
msgid "Queen"
msgstr "Reine"

#. [unit_type]: id=Queen, race=human, gender=female
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Asheviere.cfg:14
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"While some queens are influential leaders, many others have their role "
"restricted to mere social companionship.\n"
"\n"
"Nevertheless, even when she does not share political and military power with "
"the king, a queen can still take part in the kingdom’s internal politics, "
"both by influencing the royal court and through her kinship with the royal "
"family."
msgstr ""
"Si certaines reines exercent une influence considérable, beaucoup d'autres "
"voient leur rôle se limiter à de simples relations sociales.\n"
"\n"
"Néanmoins, même lorsqu'elle ne partage pas le pouvoir politique et militaire "
"avec le roi, une reine peut participer à la vie politique intérieure du "
"royaume, tant par son influence à la cour royale que par ses liens de "
"parenté avec la famille royale."

#. [unit_type]: id=Delfador L1, race=human
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Delfador_L1.cfg:8
msgid "Mage"
msgstr "Mage"

#. [unit_type]: id=Delfador L1, race=human
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Delfador_L1.cfg:12
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Humans have often pondered the workings of the world in which they live. "
"Some endeavor to take this beyond idle musing, to set it as the primary "
"enterprise of their lives. Any magi worthy of the title have spent at least "
"a decade in study, amassing a sum of knowledge which sets them apart from "
"other people. These men and women, who have committed themselves fully to "
"the pursuit of wisdom, stand in stark contrast to a world where few can even "
"read and write. Their ranks are filled with the children of hopeful "
"nobility, or those who sought an escape from the intellectual void of manual "
"labor.\n"
"\n"
"It is an irony that, with all their knowledge, and their unassuming monopoly "
"thereof, the collective community of magi could likely rule society, were "
"they ever to try. However, their true love is neither money, nor power, and "
"those who see the study of magic as a means to such ends often lack the very "
"conviction required for true mastery.\n"
"\n"
"Physically frail, and lacking familiarity with combat, magi do possess "
"certain arts which are of great utility in battle."
msgstr ""
"Les humains se sont souvent interrogés sur le fonctionnement du monde dans "
"lequel ils vivent. Certains vont au‑delà de ces réflexions oisives et font "
"de cette quête la principale occupation de leur vie. Tout magicien digne de "
"ce nom a consacré au moins une décennie à l’étude, accumulant un savoir qui "
"le distingue nettement du commun des mortels. Ces hommes, qui se sont "
"entièrement consacrés à la recherche de la sagesse, tranchent vivement avec "
"un monde où peu savent lire et écrire. Parmi eux, on trouve souvent les "
"enfants d’une noblesse ambitieuse, ou ceux qui cherchaient à fuir le vide "
"intellectuel du travail manuel.\n"
"\n"
"Ironie du sort : avec tout leur savoir et leur monopole discret de celui-ci, "
"la communauté des magiciens pourrait probablement gouverner la société si "
"elle le voulait. Pourtant, leur véritable passion n’est ni l’argent ni le "
"pouvoir, et ceux qui envisagent l’étude de la magie comme un simple moyen "
"d’y accéder manquent souvent de la conviction nécessaire à la maîtrise "
"véritable.\n"
"\n"
"Physiquement fragiles et peu rompus au combat, les magiciens possèdent "
"néanmoins certains arts d’une grande utilité sur le champ de bataille."

#. [attack]: type=impact
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Delfador_L1.cfg:31
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Delfador_L2.cfg:29
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Delfador_L3.cfg:32
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Delfador_L4.cfg:32
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Orcish_Adept.cfg:31
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Orcish_Shaman.cfg:31
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Orcish_Sorceress.cfg:31
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Saurian_Devotee.cfg:45
#, fuzzy
msgid "staff"
msgstr "bâton"

#. [unit_type]: id=Delfador L2, race=human
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Delfador_L2.cfg:8
#, fuzzy
msgid "Red Mage"
msgstr "Mage rouge"

#. [unit_type]: id=Delfador L2, race=human
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Delfador_L2.cfg:12
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Upon the successful culmination of their apprenticeship, a mage is stripped "
"of the brown robes of an apprentice and given the ruddy cloak of a master. "
"The significance of this change is often lost on the peasantry, who "
"mistakenly title Master Magi as ‘Red Magi’. Likewise, the symbolism of the "
"change in colors is often mistaken to signify the mage’s ability to "
"seemingly conjure fire from nothing but thin air, a trick which, although "
"undeniably useful, is viewed by the magi themselves as a crass application "
"of their hard-won knowledge.\n"
"\n"
"Though physically frail, and untrained as warriors, the ‘Red Magi’ have a "
"number of tricks up their sleeves, including the gouts of fire which may "
"have cemented their colloquial name."
msgstr ""
"À l’issue réussie de leur apprentissage, un magicien se voit retirer les "
"robes brunes d’apprenti pour revêtir le manteau rougeâtre du maître. La "
"portée de ce changement échappe souvent aux paysans, qui appellent par "
"erreur les Maîtres Magiciens « Magiciens Rouges ». De même, le symbolisme de "
"ce passage de couleurs est fréquemment interprété comme la preuve de la "
"capacité du magicien à faire apparaître le feu de nulle part, un tour qui, "
"bien qu’indéniablement utile, est considéré par les magiciens eux-mêmes "
"comme une application grossière de leur savoir durement acquis.\n"
"\n"
"Fragiles physiquement et peu entraînés au combat, les « Magiciens Rouges » "
"possèdent néanmoins toute une série de tours dans leur manche, notamment ces "
"gerbes de feu qui ont sans doute inspiré leur surnom populaire."

#. [unit_type]: id=Delfador L3, race=human
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Delfador_L3.cfg:8
#, fuzzy
msgid "Arch Mage"
msgstr "Archimage"

#. [unit_type]: id=Delfador L3, race=human
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Delfador_L3.cfg:12
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The title of Arch Mage is traditionally conferred only after a lifetime of "
"study and achievement to match. Arch Magi are often employed in positions of "
"education, or as advisors to those sensible enough to seek the fruits of "
"their wisdom. Many tend to wealthy patrons, a profitable enterprise for both "
"as, outside of the occasional thaumaturgy or word of advice, it gives the "
"mage leave to pursue their research undisturbed. From this flows the greater "
"body of human knowledge; the sciences, the philosophies, and the arts which "
"give beauty to the world at large.\n"
"\n"
"Though not trained for any sort of combat, if need arises an Arch Mage can "
"unleash the full power of their art, something which is not to be taken "
"lightly."
msgstr ""
"Le titre d’Archimage n’est traditionnellement conféré qu’après une vie "
"entière d’études et d’accomplissements équivalents. Les Archimages sont "
"souvent employés dans des fonctions pédagogiques ou comme conseillers auprès "
"de ceux assez avisés pour rechercher les fruits de leur sagesse. Beaucoup "
"sont au service de mécènes fortunés, une collaboration profitable pour les "
"deux, car, en dehors des quelques thaumaturgies ou de conseils ponctuels, "
"elle permet au magicien de poursuivre ses recherches en toute tranquillité. "
"De là découle le plus vaste corpus du savoir humain : les sciences, les "
"philosophies et les arts qui apportent beauté et harmonie au monde.\n"
"\n"
"Bien que non formés au combat, si le besoin s’en fait sentir, un Archimage "
"peut déchaîner toute la puissance de son art, un pouvoir qu’il ne faut "
"jamais sous-estimer."

#. [unit_type]: id=Delfador L4, race=human
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Delfador_L4.cfg:8
#, fuzzy
msgid "Great Mage"
msgstr "Grand mage"

#. [unit_type]: id=Delfador L4, race=human
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Delfador_L4.cfg:12
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Any person who is even considered for the title of Great Mage is quite "
"nearly a legend in their own time, and town criers have forcibly learnt "
"discretion in applying the title. Merit for the title is carefully "
"considered by a council of the leading magi of the age, and the conferment "
"of the title is given only by a majority vote. Regardless, anyone who is "
"seriously nominated for the honor of being called a Great Mage is, without "
"question, a master of their art, and has surpassed almost any of their peers "
"in skill.\n"
"\n"
"Though they are not warriors, by any means, the application of their art to "
"combat is something that often causes other soldiers to stand aside in awe."
msgstr ""
"Toute personne pressentie pour le titre de Grand Mage est souvent déjà "
"presque une légende de son vivant, et les crieurs publics ont rapidement "
"appris à faire preuve de discrétion avant d’employer ce titre. Le mérite "
"pour cette distinction est minutieusement examiné par un conseil composé des "
"magiciens les plus éminents de l’époque, et l’attribution du titre n’a lieu "
"qu’à la majorité des voix. Quoi qu’il en soit, quiconque est sérieusement "
"proposé pour l’honneur d’être appelé Grand Mage est, sans aucun doute, un "
"maître dans son art et a surpassé presque tous ses pairs en compétence.\n"
"\n"
"Bien qu’ils ne soient en aucun cas des guerriers, l’usage de leur art au "
"combat est un spectacle qui pousse souvent les autres soldats à s’écarter, "
"admiratifs."

#. [unit_type]: id=Veteran Cavalier, race=human, description=<i>
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Deoran_Elvish.cfg:8
#, fuzzy
msgid "Veteran Cavalier"
msgstr "Chevaliers de renom"

#. [unit_type]: id=Veteran Cavalier, race=human, description=<i>
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Deoran_Elvish.cfg:12
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Deoran rides an elvish horse, and has better movement and defense in forest "
"than do most mounted human units."
msgstr ""
"<i>Deoran monte un cheval elfique et bénéficie d’une meilleure mobilité et "
"d’une meilleure défense en forêt que la plupart des unités montées humaines."
"</i>\n"
"\n"
"Un dignitaire sage et habile peut, avec le temps, atteindre le rang "
"d’ambassadeur et devenir un envoyé officiel de Wesnoth. Généralement "
"stationnés dans des nations lointaines, ces diplomates excellent en "
"négociation et en commandement, et disposent de l’autorité nécessaire pour "
"conclure des traités au nom du trône.\n"
"\n"
"En temps de crise, ces commandants à la retraite peuvent être rappelés pour "
"reprendre la lance et combattre au service de leur nation. Forts de "
"l’expérience acquise dans la vie civile mais toujours maîtres de leur art "
"militaire, ces capitaines ne se laissent pas intimider, même face à une "
"opposition écrasante."

#. [unit_type]: id=Veteran Cavalier, race=human, description=<i>
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Deoran_Elvish.cfg:14
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"A wise and skilful dignitary may eventually rise to the rank of ambassador "
"and become an official envoy of Wesnoth. Typically stationed in far-off "
"nations, these diplomats excel at negotiation and leadership, and have the "
"authority to broker treaties on behalf of the throne."
msgstr ""
"Un dignitaire sage et habile peut, avec le temps, atteindre le rang "
"d’ambassadeur et devenir un envoyé officiel de Wesnoth. Généralement "
"stationnés dans des nations lointaines, ces diplomates excellent en "
"négociation et en leadership, et disposent de l’autorité nécessaire pour "
"conclure des traités au nom du trône."

#. [unit_type]: id=Veteran Cavalier, race=human, description=<i>
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Deoran_Elvish.cfg:16
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"In times of hardship, these retired commanders may be called upon to once "
"again take up their lance and fight in service of their nation. Having "
"learned from civilian life while still retaining much of their former "
"military skill, these captains are undeterred by even the most overwhelming "
"opposition."
msgstr ""
"En temps de crise, ces commandants à la retraite peuvent être rappelés pour "
"reprendre leur lance et combattre au service de leur nation. Forts de "
"l’expérience acquise dans la vie civile mais toujours maîtres de leur art "
"militaire, ces capitaines ne se laissent pas intimider, même face à une "
"opposition écrasante."

#. [attack]: type=pierce
#. [attack]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Deoran_Elvish.cfg:45
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Garard.cfg:31
#, fuzzy
msgid "lance"
msgstr "lance"

#. [attack]: type=impact
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Deoran_Elvish.cfg:57
#, fuzzy
msgid "trample"
msgstr "piétinement"

#. [attack]: type=pierce
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Deoran_Elvish.cfg:65
#, fuzzy
msgid "crossbow"
msgstr "arbalète"

#. [unit_type]: id=Hunker Eldred, race=human, gender=male
#. [unit_type]: id=King Eldred, race=human, gender=male
#. [unit_type]: id=Crown Prince, race=human, gender=male
#. [unit_type]: id=Unarmed Eldred, race=human, gender=male
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Eldred_Hunker.cfg:7
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Eldred_Magic.cfg:4
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Eldred_Prince.cfg:4
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Eldred_Unarmed.cfg:4
#, fuzzy
msgid "Crown Prince"
msgstr "Prince héritier"

#. [unit_type]: id=King Eldred, race=human, gender=male
#. [unit_type]: id=Crown Prince, race=human, gender=male
#. [unit_type]: id=Unarmed Eldred, race=human, gender=male
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Eldred_Magic.cfg:16
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Eldred_Prince.cfg:14
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Eldred_Unarmed.cfg:14
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"First in the line of succession, a Crown Prince must be ready to take "
"command at any time should misfortune befall the king. From a young age, "
"these royal heirs are trained in a variety of combat styles, honing their "
"skill at whichever weapons they show aptitude for. One uncommon "
"specialization involves both javelins and swordplay, each weapon covering "
"the weaknesses of the other."
msgstr ""
"Premier dans l’ordre de succession, la dauphin doit être prêt à prendre le "
"commandement à tout moment si le roi venait à être frappé par le malheur. "
"Dès leur plus jeune âge, ces héritiers royaux sont formés à divers styles de "
"combat, perfectionnant leur maîtrise des armes pour lesquelles ils montrent "
"une aptitude particulière. Une spécialisation peu courante combine le lancer "
"de javelots et le maniement de l’épée, chaque arme compensant les faiblesses "
"de l’autre."

#. [attack]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Eldred_Magic.cfg:29
#, fuzzy
msgid "baneblade"
msgstr "Lame de malheur"

#. [attack]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Eldred_Magic.cfg:33
#, fuzzy
msgid "shadow wave"
msgstr "onde ténébreuse"

#. [attack]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Eldred_Prince.cfg:27
#, fuzzy
msgid "sword"
msgstr "épée"

#. [attack]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Eldred_Prince.cfg:31
#, fuzzy
msgid "javelin"
msgstr "javelot"

#. [unit_type]: id=King of Wesnoth, race=human
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Garard.cfg:4
#, fuzzy
msgid "King of Wesnoth"
msgstr "Roi de Wesnoth"

#. [unit_type]: id=King of Wesnoth, race=human
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Garard.cfg:6
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Kings are trained rigorously in the combat arts, sometimes out of necessity, "
"more often out of tradition from when their priors made their wealth in war. "
"In battle, a king may wield a sword and lance, riding a steed bred more for "
"power than for speed. Royalty at the head of a cavalry charge is a "
"terrifying sight for opposing infantry, and is often enough to break right "
"through a defensive line."
msgstr ""
"Les rois sont formés rigoureusement aux arts martiaux, parfois par "
"nécessité, mais le plus souvent par une tradition héritée des souverains "
"guerriers de jadis. Sur le champ de bataille, un roi peut manier l’épée et "
"la lance, montant un destrier élevé pour sa puissance plutôt que pour sa "
"vitesse. La vue d’un souverain à la tête d’une charge de cavalerie est un "
"spectacle terrifiant pour l’infanterie ennemie et le choc résultant suffit "
"souvent à briser une ligne défensive."

#. [attack]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Human_Garard.cfg:25
#, fuzzy
msgid "longsword"
msgstr "Épée longue"

#. [dummy]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Monster_Cave_Bear.cfg:10
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Monster_Cave_Bear.cfg:18
#, fuzzy
msgid "consume"
msgstr "absorber"

#. [dummy]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Monster_Cave_Bear.cfg:11
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Monster_Cave_Bear.cfg:19
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"This unit regains <span color='#00FF00'>30%</span> of its maximum hitpoints "
"whenever it kills a living unit."
msgstr ""
"À chaque fois qu’elle élimine un ennemi, cette unité récupère <span "
"color='#00FF00'>30 %</span> de ses points de vie."

#. [unit_type]: id=Eyestalk, race=monster
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Monster_Eyestalk.cfg:4
#, fuzzy
msgid "Eyestalk"
msgstr "Tentacule oculaire"

#. [unit_type]: id=Eyestalk, race=monster
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Monster_Eyestalk.cfg:22
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Named ‘Eyestalks’ for obvious reasons, these plant-like creatures can focus "
"their gaze onto an unsuspecting victim to draw life energy straight out of "
"them to replenish their own. While readily flammable and almost defenseless "
"against melee attacks, their deadly gaze from afar is not to be "
"underestimated."
msgstr ""
"Appelées « Tentacules oculaires » pour des raisons évidentes, ces créatures "
"végétales peuvent fixer leur regard sur une victime inattentive pour en "
"extraire l’énergie vitale et se régénérer. Bien que facilement inflammables "
"et presque sans défense au corps à corps, leur regard mortel à distance ne "
"doit pas être sous-estimé."

#. [attack]: type=arcane
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Monster_Eyestalk.cfg:27
#, fuzzy
msgid "gaze"
msgstr "regard"

#. [unit_type]: id=Giant Crab, race=monster
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Monster_Giant_Crab.cfg:4
#, fuzzy
msgid "Giant Crab"
msgstr "Crabe géant"

#. [unit_type]: id=Giant Crab, race=monster
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Monster_Giant_Crab.cfg:14
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Giant Crabs are like regular crabs, only giant. Their claws are larger than "
"a horse’s leg, and their shell is thicker than most armor. But their most "
"interesting feature is their water spit, which is far more noxious than that "
"of their smaller cousins."
msgstr ""
"Les Crabes géants ressemblent à des crabes ordinaires, mais en version "
"gigantesque. Leurs pinces sont plus grandes qu’une jambe de cheval, et leur "
"carapace est plus épaisse que la plupart des armures. Leur caractéristique "
"la plus intéressante reste toutefois leur crachat d’eau,infiniment plus "
"toxique que celui de leurs plus petits cousins."

#. [attack]: type=impact
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Monster_Giant_Crab.cfg:70
#, fuzzy
msgid "spit"
msgstr "crachat"

#. [unit_type]: id=Silverback, race=monster
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Monster_Silverback.cfg:8
#, fuzzy
msgid "Silverback"
msgstr "Dos argentés"

#. [unit_type]: id=Silverback, race=monster
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Monster_Silverback.cfg:10
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"The greatest of the apes are the Silverbacks, so called for their "
"distinctive rear coloration. Smaller than an ogre but much more muscular, "
"the eldest of these creatures are said to possess the strength of a dozen "
"men."
msgstr ""
"Les plus grands des singes sont les dos argentés, ainsi nommés en raison de "
"la couleur caractéristique de leur dos. Plus petits qu’un ogre mais beaucoup "
"plus musclés, les plus âgées de ces créatures seraient dotés de la force "
"d’une douzaine d’hommes."

#. [attack]: type=impact
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Monster_Silverback.cfg:31
#, fuzzy
msgid "fist"
msgstr "poing"

#. [unit_type]: id=Orcish Adept, race=orc, gender=female
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Orcish_Adept.cfg:5
#, fuzzy
msgid "Orcish Adept"
msgstr "Adepte orque"

#. [unit_type]: id=Orcish Adept, race=orc, gender=female
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Orcish_Adept.cfg:24
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Female orcs with spiritual leanings may find themselves inducted into the "
"arts of orcish sorcery. Initially called Adepts, these newly-trained orcs "
"gain a curious influence over the shamanistic forces that separate life from "
"non-life. Directed inwards, this art gives them great resilience against "
"most forms of magic. Directed outwards, it grants them the fearsome power to "
"siphon life from their enemies.\n"
"\n"
"Although physically frail compared to other orcs this shamanistic art makes "
"even a freshly trained Adept a force to be reckoned with on the battlefield."
msgstr ""
"Les orques femelles aux inclinations spirituelles peuvent être initiées aux "
"mystères de la sorcellerie orque. D’abord appelées Adeptes, ces jeunes "
"orques apprennent à manier acquièrent les forces chamanistes qui séparent la "
"vie de la non-vie. Orienté vers elles-mêmes, cet art leur confère une grande "
"résistance à la plupart des formes de magie. Orienté vers l’extérieur, il "
"leur donne le redoutable pouvoir de siphonner la vie de leurs ennemis.\n"
"\n"
"Bien que physiquement frêle comparée aux autres orcs, ces Adeptes "
"fraîchement formées deviennent sur le champ de bataille des adversaires dont "
"il faut se méfier."

#. [attack]: type=arcane
#. [object]
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Orcish_Adept.cfg:40
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Orcish_Shaman.cfg:40
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Orcish_Sorceress.cfg:52
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/utils/spellcasting.cfg:810
#, fuzzy
msgid "siphon"
msgstr "siphon"

#. [unit_type]: id=Orcish Shaman, race=orc, gender=female
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Orcish_Shaman.cfg:5
#, fuzzy
msgid "Orcish Shaman"
msgstr "Chamane orque"

#. [unit_type]: id=Orcish Shaman, race=orc, gender=female
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Orcish_Shaman.cfg:24
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Like most sapient races, orcs often ponder the workings of the world in "
"which they live. Some endeavor to take this beyond idle musing, but the "
"violent, nomadic lifestyle of the largest orcish clans does not lend itself "
"to academic study, and the rare scholarly orc is invariably killed or "
"enslaved by their more warlike brethren.\n"
"\n"
"Orcish Shamans are rare exceptions to this rule. Respected among clans and "
"seen as a trustworthy and neutral party, Shamans serve as guardians of "
"orcish wisdom, and advisors in times of crisis — not something orcs tend to "
"otherwise tolerate. By the time an Adept is recognized as a fully-fledged "
"Shaman, she has committed to memory much of the orcs’ collective oral "
"tradition. This much-practiced wisdom has many applications, not least of "
"which is their improved ability to draw life from their foes during battle."
msgstr ""
"À l’instar de la plupart des races douées de raison, les orques "
"s’interrogent sur les rouages du monde qui les entoure. Certains cherchent à "
"aller au-delà de ces simples réflexions, mais le mode de vie violent et "
"nomade des plus grands clans orques ne se prête pas aux études académiques, "
"et le rare orque érudit est invariablement tué ou réduit en esclavage par "
"ses frères plus belliqueux.\n"
"\n"
"Les chamanes orques constituent de rares exceptions à cette règle. "
"Respectées au sein des clans et considérés comme des médiatrices fiables et "
"impartiales, les chamanes servent de gardiennes de la sagesse orque et de "
"conseillères en temps de crise — rôle que les orques tolèrent rarement "
"autrement. Lorsqu’une adepte est reconnue comme chamane accomplie, elle a "
"mémorisé une grande partie de la tradition orale collective des orques. "
"Cette sagesse, maintes fois pratiquée, a de nombreuses usages, dont une "
"aptitude particulière à extraire la force vitale de leurs ennemis au combat."

#. [unit_type]: id=Orcish Sorceress, race=orc, gender=female
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Orcish_Sorceress.cfg:5
#, fuzzy
msgid "Orcish Sorceress"
msgstr "Sorcière orque"

#. [unit_type]: id=Orcish Sorceress, race=orc, gender=female
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Orcish_Sorceress.cfg:24
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Orcs are sometimes capable of living as long as humans, but very few "
"individuals ever fully realize that potential, as the average orc only sees "
"two or three decades before meeting their end either in war or by the hand "
"of one of their kin. Only the Shamans, isolated from the daily strife of the "
"major orcish clans, commonly live to reach old age.\n"
"\n"
"The greatest of these elders make up the Great Council, which may arbitrate "
"the many conflicts that arise between clans of their argumentative brethren. "
"Having practiced their mystical art to perfection, these aged orcs are held "
"in the highest respect across the various clans."
msgstr ""
"Les orques peuvent parfois vivre aussi longtemps que les humains, mais très "
"peu atteignent cet âge, car un orque moyen ne dépasse rarement deux ou trois "
"décennies avant de mourir, que ce soit à la guerre ou de la main d’un autre "
"orque. Seuls les chamanes, à l’écart des querelles du quotidien des grands "
"clans orques, vivent habituellement jusqu’à un âge avancé.\n"
"\n"
"Les plus illustres de ces sages forment le Grand Conseil, qui arbitre les "
"conflits fréquents entre les clans de leurs frères querelleurs. Ayant "
"perfectionné leur magie au fil des années, ces orques âgées sont hautement "
"respectées dans tous les clans."

#. [attack]: type=arcane
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Orcish_Sorceress.cfg:40
#, fuzzy
msgid "sap"
msgstr "saper"

#. [unit_type]: id=Beacon, race=mechanical
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Saurian_Beacon.cfg:5
#, fuzzy
msgid "Beacon"
msgstr "Flambeau"

#. [unit_type]: id=Saurian Devotee, race=lizard, gender=male
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Saurian_Devotee.cfg:23
#, fuzzy
msgid "Saurian Devotee"
msgstr "Dévot saurien"

#. [unit_type]: id=Saurian Devotee, race=lizard, gender=male
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Saurian_Devotee.cfg:37
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"Young saurians particularly keen on the magical arts are trained as "
"Devotees. Although they still lack the strength of Augurs and Prophets, they "
"can still use their abilities to defend their clan in times of need."
msgstr ""
"Les jeunes sauriens particulièrement doués pour les arts magiques sont "
"formés en tant que Dévots. Bien qu’ils ne possèdent pas encore la force des "
"Augures et des Prophètes, ils peuvent néanmoins utiliser leurs capacités "
"pour défendre leur clan en cas de besoin."

#. [attack]: type=cold
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Saurian_Devotee.cfg:54
#, fuzzy
msgid "curse"
msgstr "malédiction"

#. [unit_type]: id=Saurian Juvenile, race=lizard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Saurian_Juvenile.cfg:5
#, fuzzy
msgid "Saurian Juvenile"
msgstr "Saurien juvénile"

#. [unit_type]: id=Saurian Juvenile, race=lizard
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Saurian_Juvenile.cfg:15
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"These young saurians are less than a year old, and are too weak and infirm "
"to hunt or fight. Older Juveniles may tend to a few basic duties within "
"their clutch, but are still defenceless in combat. As these saurians grow "
"older, they will quickly learn to fend for themselves and become fully grown "
"adults by the age of three."
msgstr ""
"Ces jeunes sauriens ont moins d’un an et ne sont pas assez forts pour "
"chasser ou se battre. Les juvéniles plus âgés peuvent remplir certaines "
"tâches basiques au sein de la couvée, mais restent incapables de se défendre "
"au combat. En grandissant, ils apprendront à survivre par eux-mêmes et "
"atteindront l’âge adulte complet à trois ans."

#. [unit_type]: id=Saurian Spike, race=lizard, gender=female
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Saurian_Young.cfg:23
#, fuzzy
msgid "Saurian Spike"
msgstr "Pic Saurien"

#. [unit_type]: id=Saurian Spike, race=lizard, gender=female
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Saurian_Young.cfg:37
#, fuzzy
msgid ""
"These young saurians are still learning to wield a proper spear, and have "
"not yet attained the skills of their elders. They are skilled enough to hunt "
"small animals, but are still unprepared for a true battle, fighting only on "
"the most dire occasions."
msgstr ""
"Ces jeunes sauriens apprennent encore à manier correctement la lance et "
"n'ont pas encore acquis l'habileté de leurs aînés. Ils sont suffisamment "
"habiles pour chasser le petit gibier, mais ne sont pas encore préparés au "
"combat et ne se battent qu'en cas d'extrême nécessité."

#. [attack]: type=pierce
#: data/campaigns/The_Deceivers_Gambit/units/Saurian_Young.cfg:45
msgid "spear"
msgstr "lance"

